#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:97
msgid "fish 4.3.0 (released December 28, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:101
msgid ""
"fish no longer sets user-facing :ref:`universal variables <variables-"
"universal>` by default, making the configuration easier to understand. "
"Specifically, the ``fish_color_*``, ``fish_pager_color_*`` and "
"``fish_key_bindings`` variables are now set in the global scope by default. "
"After upgrading to 4.3.0, fish will (once and never again) migrate these "
"universals to globals set at startup in the ``~/.config/fish/conf.d/"
"fish_frozen_theme.fish`` and ``~/.config/fish/conf.d/"
"fish_frozen_key_bindings.fish`` files. We suggest that you delete those "
"files and :ref:`set your theme <syntax-highlighting>` in ``~/.config/fish/"
"config.fish``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:108
msgid ""
"You can still configure fish to propagate theme changes instantly; see :ref:"
"`here <syntax-highlighting-instant-update>` for an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:109
msgid ""
"You can still opt into storing color variables in the universal scope via "
"``fish_config theme save`` though unlike ``fish_config theme choose``, it "
"does not support dynamic theme switching based on the terminal's color theme "
"(see below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:112
msgid ""
"In addition to setting the variables which are explicitly defined in the "
"given theme, ``fish_config theme choose`` now clears only color variables "
"that were set by earlier invocations of a ``fish_config theme choose`` "
"command (which is how fish's default theme is set)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:117 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:305
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:645 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:861
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1007 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1125
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1353 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1509
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1696 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1908
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2459
msgid "Scripting improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:118
msgid ""
"New :ref:`status language <status-language>` command allows showing and "
"modifying language settings for fish messages without having to modify "
"environment variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:119
msgid ""
"When using a noninteractive fish instance to compute completions, "
"``commandline --cursor`` works as expected instead of throwing an error (:"
"issue:`11993`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:120
msgid ""
":envvar:`fish_trace` can now be set to ``all`` to also trace execution of "
"key bindings, event handlers as well as prompt and title functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:124
msgid ""
"When typing immediately after starting fish, the first prompt is now "
"rendered correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:125
msgid ""
"Completion accuracy was improved for file paths containing ``=`` or ``:`` (:"
"issue:`5363`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:126
msgid ""
"Prefix-matching completions are now shown even if they don't match the case "
"typed by the user (:issue:`7944`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:127
msgid ""
"On Cygwin/MSYS, command name completion will favor the non-exe name "
"(``foo``) unless the user started typing the extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:128
msgid ""
"When using the exe name (``foo.exe``), fish will use the description and "
"completions for ``foo`` if there are none for ``foo.exe``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:129
msgid "Autosuggestions now also show soft-wrapped portions (:issue:`12045`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:133
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-w` (``backward-kill-path-component``) also deletes escaped spaces "
"(:issue:`2016`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:134
msgid ""
"New special input functions ``backward-path-component``, ``forward-path-"
"component`` and ``kill-path-component`` (:issue:`12127`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:138
msgid ""
"Themes can now be made color-theme-aware by including both ``[light]`` and "
"``[dark]`` sections in the :ref:`theme file <fish-config-theme-files>`. Some "
"default themes have been made color-theme-aware, meaning they dynamically "
"adjust as your terminal's background color switches between light and dark "
"colors (:issue:`11580`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:140
msgid ""
"The working directory is now reported on every fresh prompt (via OSC 7), "
"fixing scenarios where a child process (like ``ssh``) left behind a stale "
"working directory (:issue:`12191`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:141
msgid ""
"OSC 133 prompt markers now also mark the prompt end, which improves shell "
"integration with terminals like iTerm2 (:issue:`11837`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:142
msgid ""
"Operating-system-specific key bindings are now decided based on the :ref:"
"`terminal's host OS <status-terminal-os>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:143
msgid ""
"New :ref:`feature flag <featureflags>` ``omit-term-workarounds`` can be "
"turned on to prevent fish from trying to work around some incompatible "
"terminals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:147
msgid ""
"Tarballs no longer contain prebuilt documentation, so building and "
"installing documentation requires Sphinx. To avoid users accidentally losing "
"docs, the ``BUILD_DOCS`` and ``INSTALL_DOCS`` configuration options have "
"been replaced with a new ``WITH_DOCS`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:150
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader`` and ``fish_indent`` are now installed as hardlinks to "
"``fish``, to save some space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:154
msgid "(from 4.1.0) Crash on incorrectly-set color variables (:issue:`12078`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:155
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) Crash when autosuggesting Unicode characters with nontrivial "
"lowercase mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:156
msgid "(from 4.2.0) Incorrect emoji width computation on macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:157
msgid ""
"(from 4.2.0) Mouse clicks and :kbd:`ctrl-l` edge cases in multiline command "
"lines (:issue:`12121`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:158
msgid ""
"(from 4.2.0) Completions for Git remote names on some non-glibc systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:159
msgid "(from 4.2.0) Expansion of ``~$USER``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:162
msgid "fish 4.2.1 (released November 13, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:164
msgid "This release fixes the following problems identified in 4.2.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:166
msgid ""
"When building from a tarball without Sphinx (that is, with ``-"
"DBUILD_DOCS=OFF`` or when ``sphinx-build`` is not found), builtin man pages "
"and help files were missing, which has been fixed (:issue:`12052`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:168
msgid ""
"``fish_config``'s theme selector (the \"colors\" tab) was broken, which has "
"been fixed (:issue:`12053`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:171
msgid "fish 4.2.0 (released November 10, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:174 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:273
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:575 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:844
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:994 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1067
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1294 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1454
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1685 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1846
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2392
msgid "Notable improvements and fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:175
msgid "History-based autosuggestions now include multi-line commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:176
msgid ""
"A :ref:`transient prompt <transient-prompt>` containing more lines than the "
"final prompt will now be cleared properly (:issue:`11875`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:177
msgid "Taiwanese Chinese translations have been added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:178
msgid "French translations have been supplemented (:issue:`11842`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:182
msgid ""
"fish now assumes UTF-8 for character encoding even if the system does not "
"have a UTF-8 locale. Input bytes which are not valid UTF-8 are still round-"
"tripped correctly. For example, file paths using legacy encodings can still "
"be used, but may be rendered differently on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:186
msgid ""
"On systems where no multi-byte locale is available, fish will no longer fall "
"back to using ASCII replacements for :ref:`Unicode characters <term-compat-"
"unicode-codepoints>` such as \"…\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:191
msgid ""
"The title of the terminal tab can now be set separately from the window "
"title by defining the :doc:`fish_tab_title <cmds/fish_tab_title>` function (:"
"issue:`2692`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:192
msgid ""
"fish now hides the portion of a multiline prompt that is scrolled out of "
"view due to a huge command line. This prevents duplicate lines after "
"repainting with partially visible prompt (:issue:`11911`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:193
msgid ""
":doc:`fish_config prompt <cmds/fish_config>`'s ``choose`` and ``save`` "
"subcommands have been taught to reset :doc:`fish_mode_prompt <cmds/"
"fish_mode_prompt>` in addition to the other prompt functions (:issue:"
"`11937`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:194
msgid ""
"fish no longer force-disables mouse capture (DECSET/DECRST 1000), so you can "
"use those commands to let mouse clicks move the cursor or select completions "
"items (:issue:`4918`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:197
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`alt-p` binding no longer adds a redundant space to the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:198
msgid ""
"When run as a login shell on macOS, fish now sets :envvar:`MANPATH` "
"correctly when that variable was already present in the environment (:issue:"
"`10684`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:199
msgid ""
"A Windows-specific case of the :doc:`web-based config <cmds/fish_config>` "
"failing to launch has been fixed (:issue:`11805`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:200
msgid ""
"A MSYS2-specific workaround for Konsole and WezTerm has been added, to "
"prevent them from using the wrong working directory when opening new tabs (:"
"issue:`11981`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:205
msgid ""
"Release tags and source code tarballs are GPG-signed again (:issue:`11996`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:206
msgid ""
"Documentation in release tarballs is now built with the latest version of "
"Sphinx, which means that pre-built man pages include :ref:`OSC 8 hyperlinks "
"<term-compat-osc-8>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:208
msgid ""
"The Sphinx dependency is now specified in ``pyproject.toml``, which allows "
"you to use `uv <https://github.com/astral-sh/uv>`__ to provide Sphinx for "
"building documentation (e.g. ``uv run cargo install --path .``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:210
msgid "The minimum supported Rust version (MSRV) has been updated to 1.85."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:211
msgid ""
"The standalone build mode has been made the default. This means that the "
"files in ``$CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX/share/fish`` will not be used anymore, "
"except for HTML docs. As a result, future upgrades will no longer break "
"running shells if one of fish's internal helper functions has been changed "
"in the updated version. For now, the data files are still installed "
"redundantly, to prevent upgrades from breaking already-running shells (:"
"issue:`11921`). To reverse this change (which should not be necessary), "
"patch out the ``embed-data`` feature from ``cmake/Rust.cmake``. This option "
"will be removed in future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:220
msgid ""
"OpenBSD 7.8 revealed an issue with fish's approach for displaying builtin "
"man pages, which has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:224
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) Fix the :doc:`web-based config <cmds/fish_config>` for Python "
"3.9 and older (:issue:`12039`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:225
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) Correct wrong terminal modes set by ``fish -c 'read; cat`` (:"
"issue:`12024`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:226
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) On VTE-based terminals, stop redrawing the prompt on resize "
"again, to avoid glitches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:227
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) On MSYS2, fix saving/loading of universal variables (:issue:"
"`11948`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:228
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) Fix error using ``man`` for the commands ``!`` ``.`` ``:`` "
"``[`` ``{`` (:issue:`11955`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:229
msgid "(from 4.1.0) Fix build issues on illumos systems (:issue:`11982`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:230
msgid ""
"(from 4.1.0) Fix crash on invalid :doc:`function <cmds/function>` command (:"
"issue:`11912`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:231
msgid ""
"(from 4.0.0) Fix build on SPARC and MIPS Linux by disabling ``SIGSTKFLT``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:232
msgid ""
"(from 4.0.0) Fix crash when passing negative PIDs to builtin :doc:`wait "
"<cmds/wait>` (:issue:`11929`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:233
msgid ""
"(from 4.0.0) On Linux, fix :doc:`status fish-path <cmds/status>` output when "
