#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:242
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where focus events (currently only enabled in ``tmux``) would "
"cause multiline prompts to be redrawn in the wrong line (:issue:`11870`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:243
msgid ""
"Stopped printing output that would cause a glitch on old versions of "
"Midnight Commander (:issue:`11869`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:244
msgid ""
"Added a fix for some configurations of Zellij where :kbd:`escape` key "
"processing was delayed (:issue:`11868`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:245
msgid ""
"Fixed a case where the :doc:`web-based configuration tool <cmds/"
"fish_config>` would generate invalid configuration (:issue:`11861`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:246
msgid ""
"Fixed a case where pasting into ``fish -c read`` would fail with a noisy "
"error (:issue:`11836`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:247
msgid ""
"Fixed a case where upgrading fish would break old versions of fish that were "
"still running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:249
msgid ""
"In general, fish still needs to be restarted after it is upgraded, except "
"for `standalone builds <https://github.com/fish-shell/fish-shell/?tab=readme-"
"ov-file#building-fish-with-embedded-data-experimental>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:253
msgid "fish 4.1.1 (released September 30, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:257
msgid ""
"Many of our new Chinese translations were more confusing than helpful; they "
"have been fixed or removed (:issue:`11833`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:259
msgid ""
"Note that you can work around this type of issue by configuring fish's :doc:"
"`message localization <cmds/_>`: if your environment contains something like "
"``LANG=zh_CN.UTF-8``, you can use ``set -g LC_MESSAGES en`` to use English "
"messages inside fish. This will not affect fish's child processes unless "
"``LC_MESSAGES`` was already exported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:264
msgid ""
"Some :doc:`fish_config <cmds/fish_config>` subcommands for showing prompts "
"and themes had been broken in standalone Linux builds (those using the "
"``embed-data`` cargo feature), which has been fixed (:issue:`11832`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:265
msgid ""
"On Windows Terminal, we observed an issue where fish would fail to read the "
"terminal's response to our new startup queries, causing noticeable lags and "
"a misleading error message. A workaround has been added (:issue:`11841`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:266
msgid ""
"A WezTerm `issue breaking shifted key input <https://github.com/wezterm/"
"wezterm/issues/6087>`__ has resurfaced on some versions of WezTerm; our "
"workaround has been extended to cover all versions for now (:issue:`11204`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:267
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash in :doc:`the web-based configuration tool <cmds/fish_config>` "
"when using the new underline styles (:issue:`11840`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:270
msgid "fish 4.1.0 (released September 27, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:274
msgid ""
"Compound commands (``begin; echo 1; echo 2; end``) can now be written using "
"braces (``{ echo1; echo 2 }``), like in other shells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:275
msgid ""
"fish now supports transient prompts: if :envvar:`fish_transient_prompt` is "
"set to 1, fish will reexecute prompt functions with the ``--final-"
"rendering`` argument before running a commandline (:issue:`11153`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:276
msgid ""
"Tab completion results are truncated up to the common directory path, "
"instead of somewhere inside that path. E.g. if you complete \"share/"
"functions\", and it includes the files \"foo.fish\" and \"bar.fish\", the "
"completion pager will now show \"…/foo.fish\" and \"…/bar.fish\" (:issue:"
"`11250`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:278
msgid ""
"Self-installing builds as created by e.g. ``cargo install`` no longer "
"install other files, see :ref:`below <changelog-4.1-embedded>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:279
msgid ""
"Our gettext-based message-localization has been reworked, adding "
"translations to self-installing builds; see :ref:`below <changelog-4.1-"
"gettext>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:284
msgid ""
"``set_color --background=COLOR`` no longer implicitly activates bold mode. "
"If your theme is stored in universal variables (the historical default), "
"some bold formatting might be lost. To fix this, we suggest updating to the "
"latest version of our theme, to explicitly activate bold mode, for example "
"use ``fish_config theme save \"fish default\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:288
msgid ""
"``{echo,echo}`` or ``{ echo, echo }`` are no longer interpreted as brace "
"expansion tokens but as :doc:`compound commands <cmds/begin>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:289
msgid ""
"Terminfo-style key names (``bind -k nul``) are no longer supported. They had "
"been superseded by fish's :doc:`own key names <cmds/bind>` since 4.0 (:issue:"
"`11342`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:290
msgid ""
"fish no longer reads the terminfo database, so its behavior is generally no "
"longer affected by the :envvar:`TERM` environment variable (:issue:`11344`). "
"For the time being, this change can be reversed via the ``ignore-terminfo`` :"
"ref:`feature flag <featureflags>`. To do so, run the following once and "
"restart fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:294
msgid "set -Ua fish_features no-ignore-terminfo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:296
msgid ""
"The ``--install`` option when fish is built as self-installing is removed, "
"see :ref:`below <changelog-4.1-embedded>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:297
msgid ""
"``set_color ff0000`` now outputs 24-bit RGB true-color even if :envvar:"
"`COLORTERM` is unset. One can override this by setting :envvar:"
"`fish_term24bit` to 0 (:issue:`11372`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:299
msgid ""
"fish now requires the terminal to respond to queries for the :ref:`Primary "
"Device Attribute <term-compat-primary-da>`. For now, this can be reversed "
"via a :ref:`feature flag <featureflags>`, by running (once) ``set -Ua "
"fish_features no-query-term`` and restarting fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:302
msgid ""
"Users of GNU screen may experience :ref:`minor glitches <term-compat-dcs-gnu-"
"screen>` when starting fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:306
msgid ""
"The :doc:`argparse <cmds/argparse>` builtin has seen many improvements, see :"
"ref:`below <changelog-4.1-argparse>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:307
msgid ""
"The :doc:`string pad <cmds/string-pad>` command now has a ``-C/--center`` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:308
msgid ""
"The :doc:`psub <cmds/psub>` command now allows combining ``--suffix`` with "
"``--fifo`` (:issue:`11729`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:309
msgid ""
"The :doc:`read <cmds/read>` builtin has learned the ``--tokenize-raw`` "
"option to tokenize without quote removal (:issue:`11084`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:313
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions are now also provided in multi-line command lines. Like :kbd:"
"`ctrl-r`, these operate only on the current line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:314
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions used to not suggest multi-line command-lines from history; "
"now autosuggestions include individual lines from multi-line command-lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:315
msgid ""
"The history pager search now preserves ordering between :kbd:`ctrl-s` "
"forward and :kbd:`ctrl-r` backward searches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:316
msgid ""
"Instead of highlighting events by flashing *all text to the left of the "
"cursor*, failing history token search (:kbd:`alt-.`) flashes the associated "
"token, failing tab-completion flashes the to-be-completed token (:issue:"
"`11050`), deleting an autosuggestion (:kbd:`shift-delete`) flashes the "
"suggestion, and all other scenarios flash the full command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:321
msgid ""
"Pasted commands are now stripped of any :code:`$\\ ` command prefixes, to "
"help pasting code snippets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:322
msgid ""
"Builtin help options (e.g. ``abbr --help``) now use ``man`` directly, "
"meaning that variables like :envvar:`MANWIDTH` are respected (:issue:"
"`11786`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:323
msgid ""
"``funced`` will now edit copied functions directly, instead of the file "
"where ``function --copy`` was invoked. (:issue:`11614`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:324
msgid ""
"Added a simple ``fish_jj_prompt`` which reduces visual noise in the prompt "
"inside `Jujutsu <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/>`__ repositories that "
"are colocated with Git."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:328
msgid ""
"On non-macOS systems, :kbd:`alt-left`, :kbd:`alt-right`, :kbd:`alt-"
"backspace` and :kbd:`alt-delete` no longer operate on punctuation-delimited "
"words but on whole arguments, possibly including special characters like ``/"
"`` and quoted spaces. On macOS, the corresponding :kbd:`ctrl-` prefixed keys "
"operate on whole arguments. Word operations are still available via the "
"other respective modifier, just like in most web browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:331
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-z` (undo) after executing a command will restore the previous "
"cursor position instead of placing the cursor at the end of the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:332
msgid "The :kbd:`alt-s` binding will now also use ``run0`` if available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:333
msgid ""
"Some mouse support has been added: the OSC 133 prompt marking feature has "
"learned about kitty's ``click_events=1`` flag, which allows moving fish's "
"cursor by clicking in the command line, and selecting pager items (:issue:"
"`10932`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:335
msgid ""
"Before clearing the screen and redrawing, :kbd:`ctrl-l` now pushes all text "
"located above the prompt to the terminal's scrollback, via a new special "
"input function :ref:`scrollback-push <special-input-functions-scrollback-"
"push>`. For compatibility with terminals that do not implement ECMA-48's :"
"ref:`SCROLL UP <term-compat-indn>` command, this function is only used if "
"the terminal advertises support for that via :ref:`XTGETTCAP <term-compat-"
"xtgettcap>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:339
msgid ""
"Vi mode has learned :kbd:`ctrl-a` (increment) and :kbd:`ctrl-x` (decrement) "
"(:issue:`11570`)."
msgstr ""

