#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:458
msgid "fish 4.0.6 (released September 12, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:460
msgid "This release of fish fixes a number of issues identified in fish 4.0.2:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:462
msgid "fish now properly inherits $PATH under Windows WSL2 (:issue:`11354`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:463
msgid "Remote filesystems are detected properly again on non-Linux systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:464
msgid ""
"the :doc:`printf <cmds/printf>` builtin no longer miscalculates width of "
"multi-byte characters (:issue:`11412`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:465
msgid ""
"For many years, fish has been \"relocatable\" -- it was possible to move the "
"entire ``CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX`` and fish would use paths relative to its "
"binary. Only gettext locale paths were still determined purely at compile "
"time, which has been fixed."
