#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:467
msgid ""
"the :doc:`commandline <cmds/commandline>` builtin failed to print the "
"commandline set by a ``commandline -C`` invocation, which broke some "
"completion scripts. This has been corrected (:issue:`11423`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:469
msgid ""
"To work around terminals that fail to parse Operating System Command (OSC) "
"sequences, a temporary feature flag has been added. It allows you to disable "
"prompt marking (OSC 133) by running (once) ``set -Ua fish_features no-mark-"
"prompt`` and restarting fish (:issue:`11749`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:471
msgid ""
"The routines to save history and universal variables have seen some "
"robustness improvements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:472
msgid ""
"builtin :doc:`status current-command <cmds/status>` no longer prints a "
"trailing blank line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:473
msgid ""
"A crash displaying multi-line quoted command substitutions has been fixed (:"
"issue:`11444`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:474
msgid ""
"Commands like ``set fish_complete_path ...`` accidentally disabled "
"completion autoloading, which has been corrected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:475
msgid ""
"``nmcli`` completions have been fixed to query network information "
"dynamically instead of only when completing the first time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:476
msgid ""
"Git completions no longer print an error when no `git-foo` executable is in :"
"envvar:`PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:477
msgid ""
"Custom completions like ``complete foo -l long -xa ...`` that use the output "
"of ``commandline -t``. on a command-line like ``foo --long=`` have been "
"invalidated by a change in 4.0; the completion scripts have been adjusted "
"accordingly (:issue:`11508`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:479
msgid ""
"Some completions were misinterpreted, which caused garbage to be displayed "
"in the completion list. This has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:480
msgid ""
"fish no longer interprets invalid control sequences from the terminal as if "
"they were :kbd:`alt-[` or :kbd:`alt-o` key strokes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:481
msgid ""
":doc:`bind <cmds/bind>` has been taught about the :kbd:`printscreen` and :"
"kbd:`menu` keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:482
msgid ":kbd:`alt-delete` now deletes the word right of the cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:483
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-alt-h` erases the last word again (:issue:`11548`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:484
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-left` :kbd:`alt-right` were misinterpreted because they send "
"unexpected sequences on some terminals; a workaround has been added.  (:"
"issue:`11479`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:485
msgid ""
"Key bindings like ``bind shift-A`` are no longer accepted; use ``bind shift-"
"a`` or ``bind A``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:486
msgid ""
"Key bindings like ``bind shift-a`` take precedence over ``bind A`` when the "
"key event included the shift modifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:487
msgid ""
"Bindings using shift with non-ASCII letters (such as :kbd:`ctrl-shift-ä`) "
"are now supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:488
msgid ""
"Bindings with modifiers such as ``bind ctrl-w`` work again on non-Latin "
"keyboard layouts such as a Russian one. This is implemented by allowing key "
"events such as :kbd:`ctrl-ц` to match bindings of the corresponding Latin "
"key, using the kitty keyboard protocol's base layout key (:issue:`11520`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:490
msgid ""
"Vi mode: The cursor position after pasting via :kbd:`p` has been corrected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:491
msgid ""
"Vi mode: Trying to replace the last character via :kbd:`r` no longer "
"replaces the last-but-one character (:issue:`11484`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:496
msgid "fish 4.0.2 (released April 20, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:498
msgid "This release of fish fixes a number of issues identified in fish 4.0.1:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:500
msgid ""
"Completions are quoted, rather than backslash-escaped, only if the "
"completion is unambiguous. Continuing to edit the token is therefore easier "
"(:issue:`11271`). This changes the behavior introduced in 4.0.0 where all "
"completions were quoted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:501
msgid ""
"The warning when the terminfo database can't be found has been downgraded to "
"a log message. fish will act as if the terminal behaves like xterm-256color, "
"which is correct for the vast majority of cases (:issue:`11277`, :issue:"
"`11290`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:502
msgid ""
"Key combinations using the super (Windows/command) key can now (actually) be "
"bound using the :kbd:`super-` prefix (:issue:`11217`). This was listed in "
"the release notes for 4.0.1 but did not work correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:503
msgid ""
":doc:`function <cmds/function>` is stricter about argument parsing, rather "
"than allowing additional parameters to be silently ignored (:issue:`11295`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:504
msgid ""
"Using parentheses in the :doc:`test <cmds/test>` builtin works correctly, "
"following a regression in 4.0.0 where they were not recognized (:issue:"
"`11387`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:505
msgid ""
":kbd:`delete` in Vi mode when Num Lock is active will work correctly (:issue:"
"`11303`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:506
msgid ""
"Abbreviations cannot alter the command-line contents, preventing a crash (:"
"issue:`11324`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:507
msgid ""
"Improvements to various completions, including new completions for ``wl-"
"randr`` (:issue:`11301`), performance improvements for ``cargo`` completions "
"by avoiding network requests (:issue:`11347`), and other improvements for  "
"``btrfs`` (:issue:`11320`), ``cryptsetup`` (:issue:`11315`), ``git`` (:issue:"
"`11319`, :issue:`11322`, :issue:`11323`), ``jj`` (:issue:`11046`), and "
"``systemd-analyze`` (:issue:`11314`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:508
msgid ""
"The Mercurial (``hg``) prompt can handle working directories that contain an "
"embedded newline, rather than producing errors (:issue:`11348`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:509
msgid ""
"A number of crashes have been fixed. Triggers include prompts containing "
"backspace characters (:issue:`11280`), history pager search (:issue:"
"`11355`), invalid UTF-8 in :doc:`read <cmds/read>` (:issue:`11383`), and the "
"``kill-selection`` binding (:issue:`11367`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:510
msgid ""
"A race condition in the test suite has been fixed (:issue:`11254`), and a "
"test for fish versioning relaxed to support downstream distributors' "
"modifications (:issue:`11173`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:511
msgid ""
"Small improvements to the documentation (:issue:`11264`, :issue:`11329`, :"
"issue:`11361`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:516
msgid "fish 4.0.1 (released March 12, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:518
msgid ""
"This release of fish includes the following improvements compared to fish "
"4.0.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:520
msgid ""
"Key combinations using the super (Windows/command) key can be bound using "
"the :kbd:`super-` prefix (:issue:`11217`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:521
msgid ""
"Konsole's menu shows the \"Open folder with\" option again (:issue:`11198`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:522
msgid ""
"``$fish_color_search_match`` will now only be applied to the foreground "
"color if it has an explicit foreground. For example, this allows setting::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:523
msgid "set -g fish_color_search_match --reverse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:524
msgid ""
"Cursor shape commands (``\\e[2 q``) are no longer sent in non-interactive "
"shells or in redirections (:issue:`11255`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:525
msgid ""
":doc:`status <cmds/status>` gained a ``is-interactive-read`` subcommand, to "
"check whether the script is being called from an interactive :doc:`read "
"<cmds/read>` invocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:526
msgid ""
"fish's background tasks are now started in a way that avoids an error on "
"macOS Terminal.app (:issue:`11181`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:527
msgid "Using key combinations within qemu should work correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:528
msgid ""
"Prompts containing control characters no longer cause incorrect display of "
"command lines (:issue:`11252`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:529
msgid ""
"Cancelling the command-line in Vi mode displays correctly again (:issue:"
"`11261`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:530
msgid ""
"The acidhub prompt properly displays the git branch again (:issue:`11179`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:531
msgid ""
"Completions for ``wine`` correctly include files again (:issue:`11202`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:532
msgid ""
"On macOS, paths from ``/etc/paths`` and ``/etc/manpaths`` containing colons "
"are handled correctly (:issue:`10684`). This functionality was included in "
"the 4.0.0 release notes but was missing from the source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:533
msgid ""
"The XTerm ``modifyOtherKeys`` keyboard encoding is no longer used under "
"WezTerm, as it does not work correctly in all layouts (:issue:`11204`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:534
msgid ""
":kbd:`option-left` and other similar keys should now work in iTerm versions "
"before 3.5.12; the kitty keyboard protocol is now disabled on these versions "
"(:issue:`11192`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:535
msgid ""
"The kitty keyboard protocol is no longer used under Midnight Commander, as "
"it does not work correctly (:issue:`10640`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:536
msgid ""
"fish now sends the commandline along with the OSC 133 semantic prompt "
"command start sequence. This fixes a test in the kitty terminal (:issue:"
"`11203`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:537
msgid ""
"Git completions for third-party commands like \"git-absorb\" are completed "
"correctly again (:issue:`11205`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:538
msgid ""
"Completions for ``diskutil`` no longer produce an error (:issue:`11201`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:539
msgid ""
"The output of certain error messages no longer prints newlines to standard "
"output (:issue:`11248`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:540
msgid ""
"A number of crashes have been fixed, including file names longer than 255 "
"bytes (:issue:`11221`), using fish on a btrfs filesystem (:issue:`11219`), "
"history files that do not have the expected format (:issue:`11236`), and "
"pasting into an empty command line (:issue:`11256`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:545
msgid "fish 4.0.0 (released February 27, 2025)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:547
msgid ""
"fish's core code has been ported from C++ to Rust (:issue:`9512`). This "
"means a large change in dependencies and how to build fish. However, there "
"should be no direct impact on users. Packagers should see the :ref:`For "
"Distributors <rust-packaging>` section at the end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:550
msgid "Notable backwards-incompatible changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:552
msgid ""
"As part of a larger binding rework, ``bind`` gained a new key notation. In "
"most cases the old notation should keep working, but in rare cases you may "
"have to change a ``bind`` invocation to use the new notation. See :ref:"
"`below <changelog-4.0-new-bindings>` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:555
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-c` now calls a new bind function called ``clear-commandline``. "
"The old behavior, which leaves a \"^C\" marker, is available as ``cancel-"
"commandline`` (:issue:`10935`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:556
msgid ""
"``random`` will produce different values from previous versions of fish when "
"used with the same seed, and will work more sensibly with small seed "
"numbers. The seed was never guaranteed to give the same result across "
"systems, so we do not expect this to have a large impact (:issue:`9593`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:559
msgid ""
"Variables in command position that expand to a subcommand keyword are now "
"forbidden to fix a likely user error. For example, ``set editor command "
"emacs; $editor`` is no longer allowed (:issue:`10249`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:561
msgid ""
"``functions --handlers`` will now list handlers in a different order. Now it "
"is definition order, first to last, where before it was last to first. This "
"was never specifically defined, and we recommend not relying on a specific "
"order (:issue:`9944`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:564
msgid ""
"The ``qmark-noglob`` feature, introduced in fish 3.0, is enabled by default. "
"That means ``?`` will no longer act as a single-character glob. You can, for "
"the time being, turn it back on by adding ``no-qmark-noglob`` to :envvar:"
"`fish_features` and restarting fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:567
msgid "set -Ua fish_features no-qmark-noglob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:569
msgid ""
"The flag will eventually be made read-only, making it impossible to turn off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:570
msgid ""
"Terminals that fail to ignore unrecognized OSC or CSI sequences may display "
"garbage. We know cool-retro-term and emacs' ansi-term are affected, but most "
"mainstream terminals are not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:571
msgid ""
"fish no longer searches directories from the Windows system/user ``$PATH`` "
"environment variable for Linux executables. To execute Linux binaries by "
"name (i.e. not with a relative or absolute path) from a Windows folder, make "
"sure the ``/mnt/c/...`` path is explicitly added to ``$fish_user_paths`` and "
"not just automatically appended to ``$PATH`` by ``wsl.exe`` (:issue:`10506`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:572
msgid ""
"Under Microsoft Windows Subsystem for Linux 1 (not WSL 2), backgrounded jobs "
"that have not been disowned and do not terminate on their own after a "
"``SIGHUP`` + ``SIGCONT`` sequence will be explicitly killed by fish on exit "
"(after the usual prompt to close or disown them) to work around a WSL 1 "
"deficiency that sees backgrounded processes that run into ``SIGTTOU`` remain "
"in a suspended state indefinitely (:issue:`5263`). The workaround is to "
"explicitly ``disown`` processes you wish to outlive the shell session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:578
msgid ""
"fish now requests XTerm's ``modifyOtherKeys`` keyboard encoding and `kitty "
"keyboard protocol's <https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/keyboard-protocol/>`_ "
"progressive enhancements (:issue:`10359`). Depending on terminal support, "
"this allows to binding more key combinations, including arbitrary "
"combinations of modifiers :kbd:`ctrl`, :kbd:`alt` and :kbd:`shift`, and "
"distinguishing (for example) :kbd:`ctrl-i` from :kbd:`tab`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:581
msgid ""
"Additionally, ``bind`` now supports a human-readable syntax in addition to "
"byte sequences. This includes modifier names, and names for keys like :kbd:"
"`enter` and :kbd:`backspace`. For example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:585
msgid ""
"``bind up 'do something'`` binds the up-arrow key instead of a two-key "
"sequence (\"u\" and then \"p\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:586
msgid "``bind ctrl-x,alt-c 'do something'`` binds a sequence of two keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:588
msgid ""
"Any key argument that starts with an ASCII control character (like ``\\e`` "
"or ``\\cX``) or is up to 3 characters long, not a named key, and does not "
"contain ``,`` or ``-`` will be interpreted in the old syntax to keep "
"compatibility for the majority of bindings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:590
msgid ""
"Keyboard protocols can be turned off by disabling the \"keyboard-protocols\" "
"feature flag::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:592
msgid "set -Ua fish_features no-keyboard-protocols"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:594
msgid ""
"This is a temporary measure to work around buggy terminals (:issue:`11056`), "
"which appear to be relatively rare. Use this if something like \"=0\" or "
"\"=5u\" appears in your commandline mysteriously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:597
msgid ""
"fish can now be built as a self-installing binary (:issue:`10367`). That "
"means it can be easily built on one system and copied to another, where it "
"can extract supporting files. To do this, run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:600
msgid ""
"cargo install --path . # in a clone of the fish repository\n"
"# or `cargo build --release` and copy target/release/fish{,_indent,"
"_key_reader} wherever you want"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:603
msgid ""
"The first time it runs interactively, it will extract all the data files to  "
"``~/.local/share/fish/install/``. A specific path can be used for the data "
"files with ``fish --install=PATH`` To uninstall, remove the fish binaries "
"and that directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:605
msgid ""
"This build system is experimental; the main build system, using ``cmake``, "
"remains the recommended approach for packaging and installation to a prefix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:606
msgid ""
"A new function ``fish_should_add_to_history`` can be overridden to decide "
"whether a command should be added to the history (:issue:`10302`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:607
msgid ""
"Bindings can now mix special input functions and shell commands, so ``bind "
"ctrl-g expand-abbr \"commandline -i \\n\"`` works as expected (:issue:"
"`8186`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:608
msgid ""
"Special input functions run from bindings via ``commandline -f`` are now "
"applied immediately, instead of after the currently executing binding (:"
"issue:`3031`, :issue:`10126`). For example, ``commandline -i foo; "
"commandline | grep foo`` succeeds now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:610
msgid ""
"Undo history is no longer truncated after every command, but kept for the "
"lifetime of the shell process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:611
msgid "The :kbd:`ctrl-r` history search now uses glob syntax (:issue:`10131`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:612
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`ctrl-r` history search now operates only on the line or command "
"substitution at cursor, making it easier to combine commands from history (:"
"issue:`9751`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:613
msgid ""
"Abbreviations can now be restricted to specific commands. For instance::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:615
msgid "abbr --add --command git back 'reset --hard HEAD^'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:617
msgid ""
"will expand \"back\" to ``reset --hard HEAD^``, but only when the command is "
"``git`` (:issue:`9411`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:622
msgid ""
"``commandline --tokenize`` (short option ``-o``) has been deprecated in "
"favor of ``commandline --tokens-expanded`` (short option ``-x``) which "
"expands variables and other shell syntax, removing the need to use :doc:"
"`eval <cmds/eval>` in completion scripts (:issue:`10212`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:623
msgid "Two new feature flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:625
msgid ""
"``remove-percent-self`` (see ``status features``) disables PID expansion of "
"``%self``, which has been supplanted by ``$fish_pid`` (:issue:`10262`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:626
msgid ""
"``test-require-arg`` disables ``test``'s one-argument mode. That means "
"``test -n`` without an additional argument will return false, ``test -z`` "
"will keep returning true. Any other option without an argument, anything "
"that is not an option and no argument will be an error. This also goes for "
"``[``, test's alternate name. This is a frequent source of confusion and so "
"we are breaking with POSIX explicitly in this regard. In addition to the "
"feature flag, there is a debug category \"deprecated-test\". Running fish "
"with ``fish -d deprecated-test`` will show warnings whenever a ``test`` "
"invocation that would change is used. (:issue:`10365`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:630
msgid "These can be enabled with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:632
msgid "set -Ua fish_features remove-percent-self test-require-arg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:634
msgid ""
"We intend to enable them by default in future, and after that eventually "
"make them read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:635
msgid ""
"Specifying key names as terminfo names (using the ``bind -k`` syntax) is "
"deprecated and may be removed in a future version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:636
msgid ""
"When a terminal pastes text into fish using bracketed paste, fish used to "
"switch to a special ``paste`` bind mode. This bind mode has been removed. "
"The behavior on paste is no longer configurable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:638
msgid ""
"When an interactive fish is stopped or terminated by a signal that cannot be "
"caught (SIGSTOP or SIGKILL), it may leave the terminal in a state where "
"keypresses with modifiers are sent as CSI u sequences, instead of "
"traditional control characters or escape sequences that are recognized by "
"Readline and compatible programs, such as bash and python. If this happens, "
"you can use the ``reset`` command from ``ncurses`` to restore the terminal "
"state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:640
msgid "``fish_key_reader --verbose`` no longer shows timing information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:641
msgid ""
"Terminal information is no longer read from hashed terminfo databases, or "
"termcap databases (:issue:`10269`). The vast majority of systems use a non-"
"hashed terminfo database, which is still supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:642
msgid ""
"``source`` returns an error if used without a filename or pipe/redirection (:"
"issue:`10774`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:646
msgid ""
"``for`` loops will no longer remember local variables from the previous "
"iteration (:issue:`10525`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:647
msgid ""
"A new ``history append`` subcommand appends a command to the history, "
"without executing it (:issue:`4506`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:648
msgid ""
"A new redirection: ``<? /path/to/file`` will try opening the file as input, "
"and if it doesn't succeed silently uses ``/dev/null`` instead. This can help "
"with checks like ``test -f /path/to/file; and string replace foo bar < /path/"
"to/file``. (:issue:`10387`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:650
msgid ""
"A new option ``commandline --tokens-raw`` prints a list of tokens without "
"any unescaping (:issue:`10212`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:651
msgid ""
"A new option ``commandline --showing-suggestion`` tests whether an "
"autosuggestion is currently displayed (:issue:`10586`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:652
msgid ""
"``functions`` and ``type`` now show that a function was copied and its "
"source, rather than solely ``Defined interactively`` (:issue:`6575`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:653
msgid ""
"Stack trace now shows line numbers for copied functions (:issue:`6575`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:654
msgid ""
"``foo & && bar`` is now a syntax error, like in other shells (:issue:`9911`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:655
msgid "``if -e foo; end`` now prints a more accurate error (:issue:`10000`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:656
msgid ""
"``cd`` into a directory that is not readable but accessible (permissions ``--"
"x``) is now possible (:issue:`10432`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:657
msgid ""
"An integer overflow in ``string repeat`` leading to a near-infinite loop has "
"been fixed (:issue:`9899`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:658
msgid ""
"``string shorten`` behaves better in the presence of non-printable "
"characters, including fixing an integer overflow that shortened strings more "
"than intended (:issue:`9854`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:659
msgid ""
"``string pad`` no longer allows non-printable characters as padding (:issue:"
"`9854`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:660
msgid ""
"``string repeat`` now allows omission of ``-n`` when the first argument is "
"an integer (:issue:`10282`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:661
msgid ""
"``string match`` and ``replace`` have a new ``--max-matches`` option to "
"return as soon as the specified number of matches have been identified, "
"which can improve performance in scripts (:issue:`10587`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:662
msgid ""
"``functions --handlers-type caller-exit`` once again lists functions defined "
"as ``function --on-job-exit caller``, rather than them being listed by "
"``functions --handlers-type process-exit``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:663
msgid ""
"A new ``set --no-event`` option sets or erases variables without triggering "
"a variable event. This can be useful to change a variable in an event "
"handler (:issue:`10480`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:664
msgid ""
"Commas in command substitution output are no longer used as separators in "
"brace expansion, preventing a surprising expansion in some cases (:issue:"
"`5048`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:665
msgid ""
"Universal variables can now store strings containing invalid UTF-8 (:issue:"
"`10313`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:666
msgid ""
"A new ``path basename -E`` option that causes it to return the basename "
"(\"filename\" with the directory prefix removed) with the final extension "
"(if any) also removed. This is a shorter version of ``path change-extension "
"\"\" (path basename $foo)`` (:issue:`10521`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:667
msgid ""
"A new ``math --scale-mode`` option to select ``truncate``, ``round``, "
"``floor``, ``ceiling`` as you wish; the default value is ``truncate``. (:"
"issue:`9117`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:668
msgid ""
"``random`` is now less strict about its arguments, allowing a start larger "
"or equal to the end. (:issue:`10879`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:669
msgid ""
"``function --argument-names`` now produces an error if a read-only variable "
"name is used, rather than simply ignoring it (:issue:`10842`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:670
msgid ""
"Tilde expansion in braces (that is, ``{~,}``) works correctly (:issue:"
"`10610`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:674
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions were sometimes not shown after recalling a line from "
"history, which has been fixed (:issue:`10287`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:675
msgid ""
"Up-arrow search matches -- which are highlighted in reverse colors -- are no "
"longer syntax-highlighted, to fix bad contrast with the search match "
"highlighting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:676
msgid ""
"Command abbreviations (those with ``--position command`` or without a ``--"
"position``) now also expand after decorators like ``command`` (:issue:"
"`10396`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:677
msgid ""
"Abbreviations now expand after process separators like ``;`` and ``|``. This "
"fixes a regression in version 3.6 (:issue:`9730`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:678
msgid ""
"When exporting interactively defined functions (using ``type``, "
"``functions`` or ``funcsave``) the function body is now indented, to match "
"the interactive command line editor (:issue:`8603`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:679
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-x` (``fish_clipboard_copy``) on multiline commands now includes "
"indentation (:issue:`10437`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:680
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-v` (``fish_clipboard_paste``) now strips ASCII control characters "
"from the pasted text. This is consistent with normal keyboard input (:issue:"
"`5274`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:682
msgid ""
"When a command like ``fg %2`` fails to find the given job, it no longer "
"behaves as if no job spec was given (:issue:`9835`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:683
msgid ""
"Redirection in command position like ``>echo`` is now highlighted as error (:"
"issue:`8877`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:684
msgid ""
"``fish_vi_cursor`` now works properly inside the prompt created by builtin "
"``read`` (:issue:`10088`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:685
msgid ""
"fish no longer fails to open a FIFO if interrupted by a terminal resize "
"signal (:issue:`10250`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:686
msgid ""
"``read --help`` and friends no longer ignore redirections. This fixes a "
"regression in version 3.1 (:issue:`10274`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:687
msgid ""
"Measuring a command with ``time`` now considers the time taken for command "
"substitution (:issue:`9100`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:688
msgid ""
"``fish_add_path`` now automatically enables verbose mode when used "
"interactively (in the command line), in an effort to be clearer about what "
"it does (:issue:`10532`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:689
msgid "fish no longer adopts TTY modes of failed commands (:issue:`10603`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:690
msgid ""
"``complete -e cmd`` now prevents autoloading completions for ``cmd`` (:issue:"
"`6716`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:691
msgid ""
"fish's default color scheme no longer uses the color \"blue\", as it has bad "
"contrast against the background in a few terminal's default palettes (:issue:"
"`10758`, :issue:`10786`) The color scheme will not be upgraded for existing "
"installs. If you want, you should select it again via ``fish_config``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:693
msgid ""
"Command lines which are larger than the terminal are now displayed "
"correctly, instead of multiple blank lines being displayed (:issue:`7296`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:694
msgid ""
"Prompts that use external commands will no longer produce an infinite loop "
"if the command crashes (:issue:`9796`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:695
msgid ""
"The output of ``jobs`` shows \"-\" for jobs that have the same process group "
"ID as the fish process, rather than \"-2\" (:issue:`10833`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:696
msgid ""
"Job expansion (``%1`` syntax) works properly for jobs that are a mixture of "
"external commands and functions (:issue:`10832`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:697
msgid ""
"Command lines which have more lines than the terminal can be displayed and "
"edited correctly (:issue:`10827`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:698
msgid ""
"Functions that have been erased are no longer highlighted as valid commands "
"(:issue:`10866`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:699
msgid ""
"``not``, ``time``, and variable assignments (that is ``not time a=b env``) "
"is correctly recognized as valid syntax (:issue:`10890`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:700
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration removes old right-hand-side prompts again, "
"fixing a regression in fish 3.4.0 (:issue:`10675`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:701
msgid ""
"Further protection against programs which crash and leave the terminal in an "
"inconsistent state (:issue:`10834`, :issue:`11038`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:702
msgid ""
"A workaround for git being very slow on macOS has been applied, improving "
"performance after a fresh boot (:issue:`10535`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:706
msgid ""
"When the cursor is on a command that resolves to an executable script, :kbd:"
"`alt-o` will now open that script in your editor (:issue:`10266`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:707
msgid ""
"During up-arrow history search, :kbd:`shift-delete` will delete the current "
"search item and move to the next older item. Previously this was only "
"supported in the history pager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:708
msgid ""
":kbd:`shift-delete` will also remove the currently-displayed autosuggestion "
"from history, and remove it as a suggestion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:709
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-Z` (also known as :kbd:`ctrl-shift-z`) is now bound to redo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:710
msgid ""
"Some improvements to the :kbd:`alt-e` binding which edits the command line "
"in an external editor:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:712
msgid ""
"The editor's cursor position is copied back to fish. This is currently "
"supported for Vim and Kakoune."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:713
msgid ""
"Cursor position synchronization is only supported for a set of known "
"editors, which are now also detected in aliases which use ``complete --"
"wraps``. For example, use ``complete --wraps my-vim vim`` to synchronize "
"cursors when ``EDITOR=my-vim``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:714
msgid ""
"Multiline commands are indented before being sent to the editor, which "
"matches how they are displayed in fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:715
msgid ""
"The ``...-path-component`` bindings, like ``backward-kill-path-component``, "
"now treat ``#`` as part of a path component (:issue:`10271`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:716
msgid ""
"Bindings like :kbd:`alt-l` that print output in between prompts now work "
"correctly with multiline commandlines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:717
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-d` on an empty command line lists the directory history again. "
"This restores the behavior of version 2.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:718
msgid ""
"``history-prefix-search-backward`` and ``-forward`` now maintain the cursor "
"position, instead of moving the cursor to the end of the command line (:"
"issue:`10430`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:719
msgid ""
"The following keys have refined behavior if the terminal supports :ref:`the "
"new keyboard encodings <changelog-4.0-new-bindings>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:721
msgid ""
":kbd:`shift-enter` now inserts a newline instead of executing the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:722
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-backspace` now deletes the last word instead of only one "
"character (:issue:`10741`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:723
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-delete` deletes the next word (same as :kbd:`alt-d`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:724
msgid "New special input functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:726
msgid ""
"``forward-char-passive`` and ``backward-char-passive`` are like their non-"
"passive variants but do not accept autosuggestions or move focus in the "
"completion pager (:issue:`10398`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:727
msgid ""
"``forward-token``, ``backward-token``, ``kill-token``, and ``backward-kill-"
"token`` are similar to the ``*-bigword`` variants but for the whole argument "
"token (which includes escaped spaces) (:issue:`2014`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:728
msgid ""
"``clear-commandline``, which merely clears the command line, as an "
"alternative to ``cancel-commandline`` which prints ``^C`` and a new prompt (:"
"issue:`10213`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:729
msgid ""
"The ``accept-autosuggestion`` special input function now returns false when "
"there was nothing to accept (:issue:`10608`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:730
msgid ""
"Vi mode has seen some improvements but continues to suffer from the lack of "
"people working on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:732
msgid "New default cursor shapes for insert and replace mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:733
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-n` in insert mode accepts autosuggestions (:issue:`10339`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:734
msgid ""
"Outside insert mode, the cursor will no longer be placed beyond the last "
"character on the commandline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:735
msgid ""
"When the cursor is at the end of the commandline, a single :kbd:`l` will "
"accept an autosuggestion (:issue:`10286`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:736
msgid "The cursor position after pasting (:kbd:`p`) has been corrected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:737
msgid ""
"Added an additional binding, :kbd:`_`, for moving to the beginning of the "
"line (:issue:`10720`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:738
msgid ""
"When the cursor is at the start of a line, escaping from insert mode no "
"longer moves the cursor to the previous line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:739
msgid ""
"Added bindings for clipboard interaction, like :kbd:`\",+,p` and :kbd:`\",+,"
"y,y`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:740
msgid ""
"Deleting in visual mode now moves the cursor back, matching vi (:issue:"
"`10394`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:741
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`;`, :kbd:`,`, :kbd:`v`, :kbd:`V`, :kbd:`I`, and :kbd:`gU` bindings "
"work in visual mode (:issue:`10601`, :issue:`10648`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:742
msgid "Support :kbd:`%` motion (:issue:`10593`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:743
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-k` to remove the contents of the line beyond the cursor in all "
"modes (:issue:`10648`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:744
msgid ""
"Support `ab` and `ib` vi text objects. New input functions are introduced "
"``jump-{to,till}-matching-bracket`` (:issue:`1842`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:745
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`E` binding now correctly handles the last character of the word, "
"by jumping to the next word (:issue:`9700`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:749 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:894
msgid ""
"Command-specific tab completions may now offer results whose first character "
"is a period. For example, it is now possible to tab-complete ``git add`` for "
"files with leading periods. The default file completions hide these files, "
"unless the token itself has a leading period (:issue:`3707`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:750
msgid ""
"Option completion now uses fuzzy subsequence filtering, just like non-option "
"completion (:issue:`830`). This means that ``--fb`` may be completed to ``--"
"foobar`` if there is no better match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:752
msgid ""
"Completions that insert an entire token now use quotes instead of "
"backslashes to escape special characters (:issue:`5433`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:753
msgid ""
"Normally, file name completions start after the last ``:``  or ``=`` in a "
"token. This helps commands like ``rsync --files-from=``. This special "
"meaning can now disabled by escaping these separators as ``\\:`` and "
"``\\=``. This matches Bash's behavior. Note that this escaping is usually "
"not necessary since the completion engine already tries to guess whether the "
"separator is actually part of a file name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:759
msgid "Various new completion scripts and numerous updates to existing ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:760
msgid ""
"Completions could hang if the ``PAGER`` environment variable was sent to "
"certain editors on macOS, FreeBSD and some other platforms. This has been "
"fixed (:issue:`10820`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:761
msgid ""
"Generated completions are now stored in ``$XDG_CACHE_HOME/fish`` or ``~/."
"cache/fish`` by default (:issue:`10369`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:762
msgid ""
"A regression in fish 3.1, where completing a command line could change it "
"completely, has been fixed (:issue:`10904`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:766
msgid ""
"fish now marks the prompt and command-output regions (via OSC 133) to enable "
"terminal shell integration (:issue:`10352`). Shell integration shortcuts can "
"scroll to the next/previous prompt or show the last command output in a "
"pager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:768
msgid ""
"fish now reports the working directory (via OSC 7) unconditionally instead "
"of only for some terminals (:issue:`9955`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:769
msgid ""
"fish now sets the terminal window title (via OSC 0) unconditionally instead "
"of only for some terminals (:issue:`10037`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:770
msgid "Focus reporting in tmux is no longer disabled on the first prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:771
msgid ""
"Focus reporting is now disabled during commands run inside key bindings (:"
"issue:`6942`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:772
msgid ""
"Cursor changes are applied to all terminals that support them, and the list "
"of specifically-supported terminals has been removed (:issue:`10693`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:773
msgid ""
"If it cannot find the terminfo entry given by :envvar:`TERM` environment "
"variable, fish will now use an included ``xterm-256color`` definition to "
"match the vast majority of current terminal emulators (:issue:`10905`). If "
"you need to have a specific terminfo profile for your terminal's ``TERM`` "
"variable, install it into the terminfo database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:774
msgid ""
"Further improvements to the correct display of prompts which fill the width "
"of the terminal (:issue:`8164`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:778
msgid ""
"``status`` gained a ``build-info`` subcommand, to print information on how "
"fish was built, to help with debugging (:issue:`10896`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:779
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` will now collapse multiple empty lines into one (:issue:"
"`10325`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:780
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` now preserves the modification time of files if there were "
"no changes (:issue:`10624`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:781
msgid ""
"Performance in launching external processes has been improved for many cases "
"(:issue:`10869`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:782
msgid ""
"Performance and interactivity under Windows Subsystem for Linux has been "
"improved, with a workaround for Windows-specific locations being appended to "
"``$PATH`` by default (:issue:`10506`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:783
msgid ""
"On macOS, paths from ``/etc/paths`` and ``/etc/manpaths`` containing colons "
"are handled correctly (:issue:`10684`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:784
msgid ""
"Additional filesystems such as AFS are properly detected as remote, which "
"avoids certain hangs due to expensive filesystem locks (:issue:`10818`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:785
msgid ""
"A spurious error when launching multiple instances of fish for the first "
"time has been removed (:issue:`10813`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:792
msgid ""
"fish has been ported to Rust. This means a significant change in "
"dependencies, which are listed in the README. In short, Rust 1.70 or greater "
"is required, and a C++ compiler is no longer needed (although a C compiler "
"is still required, for some C glue code and the tests)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:794
msgid ""
"CMake remains the recommended build system, because of cargo's limited "
"support for installing support files. Version 3.5 remains the minimum "
"supported version. The Xcode generator for CMake is not supported any longer "
"(:issue:`9924`). CMake builds default to optimized release builds (:issue:"
"`10799`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:796
msgid ""
"fish no longer depends on the ncurses library, but still uses a terminfo "
"database. When packaging fish, please add a dependency on the package "
"containing your terminfo database instead of curses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:798
msgid ""
"The ``test`` target was removed as it can no longer be defined in new CMake "
"versions. Use ``make fish_run_tests``. Any existing test target will not "
"print output if it fails (:issue:`11116`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:800
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration has been rewritten to use Alpine.js (:issue:"
"`9554`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:805
msgid "fish 4.0b1 (released December 17, 2024)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:807
msgid ""
"A number of improvements were included in fish 4.0.0 following the beta "
"release of 4.0b1. These include fixes for regressions, improvements to "
"completions and documentation, and the removal of a small number of "
"problematic changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:809
msgid ""
"The full list of fixed issues can be found on the `GitHub milestone page for "
"4.0-final <https://github.com/fish-shell/fish-shell/milestone/43>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:814
msgid "fish 3.7.1 (released March 19, 2024)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:816
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes the following problems identified in fish 3.7.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:818
msgid ""
"Deleting the last history entry via ``history delete`` works again (:issue:"
"`10190`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:819
msgid ""
"Wildcards (``*``) will no longer sometimes generate paths that did not exist "
"(:issue:`10205`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:821
msgid "This release also contains some improvements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:823
msgid ""
"A crash when trying to run an ELF program with a missing interpreter has "
"been fixed. This crashed in the process after fork, so did not affect the "
"fish process that tried to start the program (:issue:`10199`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:824
msgid ""
"``funced`` will now always ``source`` the file after it has written it, even "
"if the contents did not change. This prevents issues if the file was "
"otherwise modified (:issue:`10318`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:825
msgid ""
"The warning for when a builtin returns a negative exit code was improved, "
"now mentioning the original status (:issue:`10187`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:826 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2139
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2715 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3187
msgid "Added completions for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:828
msgid "``cobra-cli`` (:issue:`10293`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:829
msgid "``dmidecode`` (:issue:`10368`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:830
msgid "``mycli`` (:issue:`10309`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:831
msgid "``ollama`` (:issue:`10327`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:832
msgid "``pstree`` (:issue:`10317`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:834
msgid "Some improvements to documentation and completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:839
msgid "fish 3.7.0 (released January 1, 2024)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:841
msgid ""
"This release of fish includes a number of improvements over fish 3.6.4, "
"detailed below. Although work continues on the porting of fish internals to "
"the Rust programming language, that work is not included in this release. "
"fish 3.7.0 and any future releases in the 3.7 series remain C++ programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:845
msgid "Improvements to the history pager, including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:847
msgid ""
"The history pager will now also attempt subsequence matches (:issue:`9476`), "
"so you can find a command line like ``git log 3.6.1..Integration_3.7.0`` by "
"searching for ``gitInt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:848
msgid ""
"Opening the history pager will now fill the search field with a search "
"string if you're already in a search (:issue:`10005`). This makes it nicer "
"to search something with :kbd:`up` and then later decide to switch to the "
"full pager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:849
msgid ""
"Closing the history pager with enter will now copy the search text to the "
"commandline if there was no match, so you can continue editing the command "
"you tried to find right away (:issue:`9934`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:851
msgid ""
"Performance improvements for command completions and globbing, where "
"supported by the operating system, especially on slow filesystems such as "
"NFS (:issue:`9891`, :issue:`9931`, :issue:`10032`, :issue:`10052`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:852
msgid ""
"fish can now be configured to wait a specified amount of time for a multi-"
"key sequence to be completed,  instead of waiting indefinitely. For example, "
"this makes binding ``kj`` to switching modes in vi mode possible. The "
"timeout can be set via the new :envvar:`fish_sequence_key_delay_ms` variable "
"(:issue:`7401`), and may be set by default in future versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:857
msgid ""
"``LS_COLORS`` is no longer set automatically by the ``ls`` function (:issue:"
"`10080`). Users that set ``.dircolors`` should manually import it using "
"other means. Typically this would be ``set -gx LS_COLORS (dircolors -c ."
"dircolors | string split ' ')[3]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:862
msgid ""
"Running ``exit`` with a negative number no longer crashes fish (:issue:"
"`9659`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:863
msgid ""
"``fish --command`` will now return a non-zero status if parsing failed (:"
"issue:`9888`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:864
msgid ""
"The ``jobs`` builtin will now escape the commands it prints (:issue:`9808`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:865
msgid ""
"``string repeat`` no longer overflows if the count is a multiple of the "
"chunk size (:issue:`9900`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:866
msgid ""
"The ``builtin`` builtin will now properly error out with invalid arguments "
"instead of doing nothing and returning true (:issue:`9942`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:867
msgid ""
"``command time`` in a pipeline is allowed again, as is ``command and`` and "
"``command or`` (:issue:`9985`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:868
msgid ""
"``exec`` will now also apply variable overrides, so ``FOO=bar exec`` will "
"now set ``$FOO`` correctly (:issue:`9995`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:869
msgid ""
"``umask`` will now handle empty symbolic modes correctly, like ``umask u=,"
"g=rwx,o=`` (:issue:`10177`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:870
msgid ""
"Improved error messages for errors occurring in command substitutions (:"
"issue:`10054`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:874
msgid ""
"``read`` no longer enables bracketed paste so it doesn't stay enabled in "
"combined commandlines like ``mysql -p(read --silent)`` (:issue:`8285`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:875
msgid ""
"Vi mode now uses :envvar:`fish_cursor_external` to set the cursor shape for "
"external commands (:issue:`4656`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:876
msgid ""
"Opening the history search in vi mode switches to insert mode correctly (:"
"issue:`10141`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:877
msgid "Vi mode cursor shaping is now enabled in iTerm2 (:issue:`9698`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:878
msgid ""
"Completing commands as root includes commands not owned by root, fixing a "
"regression introduced in fish 3.2.0 (:issue:`9699`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:879
msgid ""
"Selection uses ``fish_color_selection`` for the foreground and background "
"colors, as intended, rather than just the background (:issue:`9717`)."
