#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1064
msgid "fish 3.6.0 (released January 7, 2023)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1068
msgid ""
"By default, :kbd:`ctrl-r` now opens the command history in the pager (:issue:"
"`602`). This is fully searchable and syntax-highlighted, as an alternative "
"to the incremental search seen in other shells. The new special input "
"function ``history-pager`` has been added for custom bindings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1069
msgid ""
"Abbreviations are more flexible (:issue:`9313`, :issue:`5003`, :issue:"
"`2287`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1071
msgid ""
"They may optionally replace tokens anywhere on the command line, instead of "
"only commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1072
msgid ""
"Matching tokens may be described using a regular expression instead of a "
"literal word"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1073
msgid ""
"The replacement text may be produced by a fish function, instead of a "
"literal word"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1074
msgid ""
"They may position the cursor anywhere in the expansion, instead of at the end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1076
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1078
msgid ""
"function multicd\n"
"    echo cd (string repeat -n (math (string length -- $argv[1]) - 1) ../)\n"
"end\n"
"\n"
"abbr --add dotdot --regex '^\\.\\.+$' --function multicd"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1084
msgid ""
"This expands ``..`` to ``cd ../``, ``...`` to ``cd ../../`` and ``....`` to "
"``cd ../../../`` and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1086
msgid "Or::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1088
msgid ""
"function last_history_item; echo $history[1]; end\n"
"abbr -a !! --position anywhere --function last_history_item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1091
msgid ""
"which expands ``!!`` to the last history item, anywhere on the command line, "
"mimicking other shells' history expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1093
msgid "See :doc:`the documentation <cmds/abbr>` for more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1094
msgid ""
"``path`` gained a new ``mtime`` subcommand to print the modification time "
"stamp for files. For example, this can be used to handle cache file ages (:"
"issue:`9057`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1096
msgid ""
"> touch foo\n"
"> sleep 10\n"
"> path mtime --relative foo\n"
"10"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1101
msgid ""
"``string`` gained a new ``shorten`` subcommand to shorten strings to a given "
"visible width (:issue:`9156`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1103
msgid ""
"> string shorten --max 10 \"Hello this is a long string\"\n"
"Hello thi…"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1106
msgid ""
"``test`` (aka ``[``) gained ``-ot`` (older than) and ``-nt`` (newer than) "
"operators to compare file modification times, and ``-ef`` to compare whether "
"the arguments are the same file (:issue:`3589`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1107
msgid ""
"fish will now mark the extent of many errors with a squiggly line, instead "
"of just a caret (``^``) at the beginning (:issue:`9130`). For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1109
msgid ""
"checks/set.fish (line 471): for: a,b: invalid variable name. See `help "
"identifiers`\n"
"for a,b in y 1 z 3\n"
"    ^~^"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1112
msgid ""
"A new function, ``fish_delta``, shows changes that have been made in fish's "
"configuration from the defaults (:issue:`9255`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1113
msgid ""
"``set --erase`` can now be used with multiple scopes at once, like ``set -"
"efglU foo`` (:issue:`7711`, :issue:`9280`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1114
msgid ""
"``status`` gained a new subcommand, ``current-commandline``, which retrieves "
"the entirety of the currently-executing command line when called from a "
"function during execution. This allows easier job introspection (:issue:"
"`8905`, :issue:`9296`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1118
msgid ""
"The ``\\x`` and ``\\X`` escape syntax is now equivalent. ``\\xAB`` "
"previously behaved the same as ``\\XAB``, except that it would error if the "
"value \"AB\" was larger than \"7f\" (127 in decimal, the highest ASCII "
"value) (:issue:`9247`, :issue:`9245`, :issue:`1352`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1119
msgid ""
"The ``fish_git_prompt`` will now only turn on features if the appropriate "
"variable has been set to a true value (of \"1\", \"yes\" or \"true\") "
"instead of just checking if it is defined. This allows specifically turning "
"features *off* without having to erase variables, such as via universal "
"variables. If you have defined a variable to a different value and expect it "
"to count as true, you need to change it (:issue:`9274`). For example, ``set -"
"g __fish_git_prompt_show_informative_status 0`` previously would have "
"enabled informative status (because any value would have done so), but now "
"it turns it off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1121
msgid ""
"Abbreviations are no longer stored in universal variables. Existing "
"universal abbreviations are still imported, but new abbreviations should be "
"added to ``config.fish``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1122
msgid ""
"The short option ``-r`` for abbreviations has changed from ``rename`` to "
"``regex``, for consistency with ``string``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1126
msgid ""
"``argparse`` can now be used without option specifications, to allow using "
"``--min-args``, ``--max-args`` or for commands that take no options (but "
"might in future) (:issue:`9006`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1128
msgid ""
"function my_copy\n"
"    argparse --min-args 2 -- $argv\n"
"    or return\n"
"\n"
"    cp $argv\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1135
msgid ""
"``set --show`` now shows when a variable was inherited from fish's parent "
"process, which should help with debugging (:issue:`9029`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1137
msgid ""
"> set --show XDG_DATA_DIRS\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS: set in global scope, exported, a path variable with 4 "
"elements\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS[1]: |/home/alfa/.local/share/flatpak/exports/share|\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS[2]: |/var/lib/flatpak/exports/share|\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS[3]: |/usr/local/share|\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS[4]: |/usr/share|\n"
"$XDG_DATA_DIRS: originally inherited as |/home/alfa/.local/share/flatpak/"
"exports/share:/var/lib/flatpak/exports/share:/usr/local/share/:/usr/share/|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1145
msgid ""
"The read limit is now restored to the default when :envvar:`fish_read_limit` "
"is unset (:issue:`9129`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1146
msgid ""
"``math`` produces an error for division-by-zero, as well as augmenting some "
"errors with their extent (:issue:`9190`). This changes behavior in some "
"limited cases, such as::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1148
msgid "math min 1 / 0, 5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1150
msgid ""
"which would previously print \"5\" (because in floating point division \"1 / "
"0\" yields infinite, and 5 is smaller than infinite) but will now return an "
"error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1151
msgid ""
"``fish_clipboard_copy`` and ``fish_clipboard_paste`` can now be used in "
"pipes (:issue:`9271`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1153
msgid ""
"git rev-list 3.5.1 | fish_clipboard_copy\n"
"\n"
"fish_clipboard_paste | string join + | math"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1157
msgid ""
"``status fish-path`` returns a fully-normalised path, particularly "
"noticeable on NetBSD (:issue:`9085`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1161
msgid ""
"If the terminal definition for :envvar:`TERM` can't be found, fish now tries "
"using the \"xterm-256color\" and \"xterm\" definitions before \"ansi\" and "
"\"dumb\". As the majority of terminal emulators in common use are now more "
"or less xterm-compatible (often even explicitly claiming the xterm-256color "
"entry), this should often result in a fully or almost fully usable terminal "
"(:issue:`9026`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1162
msgid ""
"A new variable, :envvar:`fish_cursor_selection_mode`, can be used to "
"configure whether the command line selection includes the character under "
"the cursor (``inclusive``) or not (``exclusive``). The new default is "
"``exclusive``; use ``set fish_cursor_selection_mode inclusive`` to get the "
"previous behavior back (:issue:`7762`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1163
msgid ""
"fish's completion pager now fills half the terminal on first tab press "
"instead of only 4 rows, which should make results visible more often and "
"save key presses, without constantly snapping fish to the top of the "
"terminal (:issue:`9105`, :issue:`2698`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1164
msgid ""
"The ``complete-and-search`` binding, used with :kbd:`shift-tab` by default, "
"selects the first item in the results immediately (:issue:`9080`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1165
msgid "``bind`` output is now syntax-highlighted when used interactively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1166
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-h` (the default ``__fish_man_page`` binding) does a better job of "
"showing the manual page of the command under cursor (:issue:`9020`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1167
msgid ""
"If :envvar:`fish_color_valid_path` contains an actual color instead of just "
"modifiers, those will be used for valid paths even if the underlying color "
"isn't \"normal\" (:issue:`9159`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1168
msgid ""
"The key combination for the QUIT terminal sequence, often :kbd:`ctrl-\\\\` "
"(``\\x1c``), can now be used as a binding (:issue:`9234`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1169
msgid ""
"fish's vi mode uses normal xterm-style sequences to signal cursor change, "
"instead of using the iTerm's proprietary escape sequences. This allows for a "
"blinking cursor and makes it work in complicated scenarios with nested "
"terminals. (:issue:`3741`, :issue:`9172`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1170
msgid ""
"When running fish on a remote system (such as inside SSH or a container), :"
"kbd:`ctrl-x` now copies to the local client system's clipboard if the "
"terminal supports OSC 52."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1171
msgid ""
"``commandline`` gained two new options, ``--selection-start`` and ``--"
"selection-end``, to set the start/end of the current selection (:issue:"
"`9197`, :issue:`9215`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1172
msgid ""
"fish's builtins now handle keyboard interrupts (:kbd:`ctrl-c`) correctly (:"
"issue:`9266`)."
msgstr ""

