#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1216
msgid ""
"Improvements to many completions, including making ``cd`` completion much "
"faster (:issue:`9220`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1217
msgid ""
"Completion of tilde (``~``) works properly even when the file name contains "
"an escaped character (:issue:`9073`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1218
msgid ""
"fish no longer loads completions if the command is used via a relative path "
"and is not in :envvar:`PATH` (:issue:`9133`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1219
msgid "fish no longer completes inside of comments (:issue:`9320`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1223
msgid ""
"Opening ``help`` on WSL now uses PowerShell to open the browser if "
"available, removing some awkward UNC path errors (:issue:`9119`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1227
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration tool now works on systems with IPv6 disabled (:"
"issue:`3857`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1228
msgid "Aliases can ignore arguments by ending them with ``#`` (:issue:`9199`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1229
msgid ""
"``string`` is now faster when reading large strings from stdin (:issue:"
"`9139`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1230
msgid "``string repeat`` uses less memory and is faster. (:issue:`9124`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1231
msgid ""
"Builtins are much faster when writing to a pipe or file. (:issue:`9229`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1232
msgid ""
"Performance improvements to highlighting (:issue:`9180`) should make using "
"fish more pleasant on slow systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1233
msgid ""
"On 32-bit systems, globs like ``*`` will no longer fail to return some "
"files, as large file support has been enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1236
msgid "Fixed bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1237
msgid ""
"The history search text for a token search is now highlighted correctly if "
"the line contains multiple instances of that text (:issue:`9066`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1238
msgid ""
"``process-exit`` and ``job-exit`` events are now generated for all "
"background jobs, including those launched from event handlers (:issue:"
"`9096`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1239
msgid ""
"A crash when completing a token that contained both a potential glob and a "
"quoted variable expansion was fixed (:issue:`9137`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1240
msgid ""
"``prompt_pwd`` no longer accidentally overwrites a global or universal "
"``$fish_prompt_pwd_full_dirs`` when called with the ``-d`` or ``--full-"
"length-dirs`` option (:issue:`9123`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1241
msgid ""
"A bug which caused fish to freeze or exit after running a command which does "
"not preserve the foreground process group was fixed (:issue:`9181`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1242
msgid ""
"The \"Disco\" sample prompt no longer prints an error in some working "
"directories (:issue:`9164`). If you saved this prompt, you should run "
"``fish_config prompt save disco`` again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1243
msgid ""
"fish launches external commands via the given path again, rather than always "
"using an absolute path. This behaviour was inadvertently changed in 3.5.0 "
"and is visible, for example, when launching a bash script which checks "
"``$0`` (:issue:`9143`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1244
msgid ""
"``printf`` no longer tries to interpret the first argument as an option (:"
"issue:`9132`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1245
msgid ""
"Interactive ``read`` in scripts will now have the correct keybindings again "
"(:issue:`9227`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1246
msgid ""
"A possible stack overflow when recursively evaluating substitutions has been "
"fixed (:issue:`9302`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1247
msgid "A crash with relative $CDPATH has been fixed (:issue:`9407`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1248
msgid ""
"``printf`` now properly fills extra ``%d`` specifiers with 0 even on macOS "
"and BSD (:issue:`9321`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1249
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader`` now correctly exits when receiving a SIGHUP (like after "
"closing the terminal) (:issue:`9309`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1250
msgid ""
"``fish_config theme save`` now works as documented instead of erroring out (:"
"issue:`9088`, :issue:`9273`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1251
msgid ""
"fish no longer triggers prompts to install command line tools when first run "
"on macOS (:issue:`9343`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1252
msgid ""
"``fish_git_prompt`` now quietly fails on macOS if the xcrun cache is not yet "
"populated (:issue:`6625`), working around a potential hang."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1256
msgid ""
"The vendored PCRE2 sources have been removed. It is recommended to declare "
"PCRE2 as a dependency when packaging fish. If the CMake variable "
"FISH_USE_SYSTEM_PCRE2 is false, fish will now download and build PCRE2 from "
"the official repo (:issue:`8355`, :issue:`8363`). Note this variable "
"defaults to true if PCRE2 is found installed on the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1261
msgid "fish 3.5.1 (released July 20, 2022)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1263
msgid "This release of fish introduces the following small enhancements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1265
msgid ""
"Cursor shaping for Vi mode is enabled by default in tmux, and will be used "
"if the outer terminal is capable (:issue:`8981`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1266
msgid ""
"``printf`` returns a better error when used with arguments interpreted as "
"octal numbers (:issue:`9035`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1267
msgid ""
"``history merge`` when in private mode is now an error, rather than wiping "
"out other sessions' history (:issue:`9050`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1268
msgid ""
"The error message when launching a command that is built for the wrong "
"architecture on macOS is more helpful (:issue:`9052`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1271
msgid "``choose`` (:issue:`9065`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1272
msgid "``expect`` (:issue:`9060`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1273
msgid "``navi`` (:issue:`9064`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1274
msgid "``qdbus`` (:issue:`9031`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1275
msgid "``reflector`` (:issue:`9027`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1277
msgid "Improvements to some completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1279
msgid "This release also fixes a number of problems identified in fish 3.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1281
msgid "Completing ``git blame`` or ``git -C`` works correctly (:issue:`9053`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1282
msgid ""
"On terminals that emit a ``CSI u`` sequence for :kbd:`shift-space`, fish "
"inserts a space instead of printing an error. (:issue:`9054`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1283
msgid ""
"``status fish-path`` on Linux-based platforms could print the path with a "
"\" (deleted)\" suffix (such as ``/usr/bin/fish (deleted)``), which is now "
"removed (:issue:`9019`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1284
msgid ""
"Cancelling an initial command (from fish's ``--init-command`` option) with :"
"kbd:`ctrl-c` no longer prevents configuration scripts from running (:issue:"
"`9024`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1285
msgid ""
"The job summary contained extra blank lines if the prompt used multiple "
"lines, which is now fixed (:issue:`9044`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1286
msgid ""
"Using special input functions in bindings, in combination with ``and``/"
"``or`` conditionals, no longer crashes (:issue:`9051`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1291
msgid "fish 3.5.0 (released June 16, 2022)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1295
msgid ""
"A new ``path`` builtin command to filter and transform paths (:issue:"
"`7659`, :issue:`8958`). For example, to list all the separate extensions "
"used on files in /usr/share/man (after removing one extension, commonly a \"."
"gz\")::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1297
msgid ""
"path filter -f /usr/share/man/** | path change-extension '' | path extension "
"| path sort -u"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1298
msgid ""
"Tab (or any key bound to ``complete``) now expands wildcards instead of "
"invoking completions, if there is a wildcard in the path component under the "
"cursor (:issue:`954`, :issue:`8593`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1299
msgid ""
"Scripts can now catch and handle the SIGINT and SIGTERM signals, either via "
"``function --on-signal`` or with ``trap`` (:issue:`6649`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1303
msgid ""
"The ``stderr-nocaret`` feature flag, introduced in fish 3.0 and enabled by "
"default in fish 3.1, has been made read-only. That means it is no longer "
"possible to disable it, and code supporting the ``^`` redirection has been "
"removed (:issue:`8857`, :issue:`8865`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1306
msgid ""
"To recap: fish used to support ``^`` to redirect stderr, so you could use "
"commands like::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1308
msgid "test \"$foo\" -gt 8 ^/dev/null"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1310
msgid ""
"to ignore error messages. This made the ``^`` symbol require escaping and "
"quoting, and was a bit of a weird shortcut considering ``2>`` already "
"worked, which is only one character longer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1312
msgid "So the above can simply become::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1314
msgid "test \"$foo\" -gt 8 2>/dev/null"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1316
msgid "The following feature flags have been enabled by default:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1318
msgid ""
"``regex-easyesc``, which makes ``string replace -r`` not do a superfluous "
"round of unescaping in the replacement expression. That means e.g. to escape "
"any \"a\" or \"b\" in an argument you can use ``string replace -ra '([ab])' "
"'\\\\\\\\$1' foobar`` instead of needing 8 backslashes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1321
msgid ""
"This only affects the *replacement* expression, not the *match* expression "
"(the ``'([ab])'`` part in the example). A survey of plugins on GitHub did "
"not turn up any affected code, so we do not expect this to affect many users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1324
msgid "This flag was introduced in fish 3.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1325
msgid ""
"``ampersand-nobg-in-token``, which means that ``&`` will not create a "
"background job if it occurs in the middle of a word. For example, ``echo "
"foo&bar`` will print \"foo&bar\" instead of running ``echo foo`` in the "
"background and then starting ``bar`` as a second job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1327
msgid ""
"Reformatting with ``fish_indent`` would already introduce spaces, turning "
"``echo foo&bar`` into ``echo foo & bar``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1329
msgid "This flag was introduced in fish 3.4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1331
msgid ""
"To turn off these flags, add ``no-regex-easyesc`` or ``no-ampersand-nobg-in-"
"token`` to :envvar:`fish_features` and restart fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1333
msgid "set -Ua fish_features no-regex-easyesc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1335
msgid "Like ``stderr-nocaret``, they will eventually be made read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1336
msgid ""
"Most ``string`` subcommands no longer append a newline to their input if the "
"input didn't have one (:issue:`8473`, :issue:`3847`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1337
msgid ""
"Fish's escape sequence removal (like for ``string length --visible`` or to "
"figure out how wide the prompt is) no longer has special support for non-"
"standard color sequences like from Data General terminals, e.g. the Data "
"General Dasher D220 from 1984. This removes a bunch of work in the common "
"case, allowing ``string length --visible`` to be much faster with unknown "
"escape sequences. We don't expect anyone to have ever used fish with such a "
"terminal (:issue:`8769`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1338
msgid ""
"Code to upgrade universal variables from fish before 3.0 has been removed. "
"Users who upgrade directly from fish versions 2.7.1 or before will have to "
"set their universal variables & abbreviations again. (:issue:`8781`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1339
msgid ""
"The meaning of an empty color variable has changed (:issue:`8793`). "
"Previously, when a variable was set but empty, it would be interpreted as "
"the \"normal\" color. Now, empty color variables cause the same effect as "
"unset variables - the general highlighting variable for that type is used "
"instead. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1341
msgid ""
"set -g fish_color_command blue\n"
"set -g fish_color_keyword"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1344
msgid ""
"would previously make keywords \"normal\" (usually white in a dark "
"terminal). Now it'll make them blue. To achieve the previous behavior, use "
"the normal color explicitly: ``set -g fish_color_keyword normal``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1346
msgid ""
"This makes it easier to make self-contained color schemes that don't "
"accidentally use color that was set before. ``fish_config`` has been "
"adjusted to set known color variables that a theme doesn't explicitly set to "
"empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1348
msgid ""
"``eval`` is now a reserved keyword, so it can't be used as a function name. "
"This follows ``set`` and ``read``, and is necessary because it can't be "
"cleanly shadowed by a function - at the very least ``eval set -l argv foo`` "
"breaks. Fish will ignore autoload files for it, so left over ``eval.fish`` "
"from previous fish versions won't be loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1349
msgid ""
"The git prompt in informative mode now defaults to skipping counting "
"untracked files, as this was extremely slow. To turn it on, set :envvar:"
"`__fish_git_prompt_showuntrackedfiles` or set the git config value \"bash."
"showuntrackedfiles\" to ``true`` explicitly (which can be done for "
"individual repositories). The \"informative+vcs\" sample prompt already "
"skipped display of untracked files, but didn't do so in a way that skipped "
"the computation, so it should be quite a bit faster in many cases (:issue:"
"`8980`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1350
msgid ""
"The ``__terlar_git_prompt`` function, used by the \"Terlar\" sample prompt, "
"has been rebuilt as a configuration of the normal ``fish_git_prompt`` to "
"ease maintenance, improve performance and add features (like reading per-"
"repo git configuration). Some slight changes remain; users who absolutely "
"must have the same behavior are encouraged to copy the old function (:issue:"
"`9011`, :issue:`7918`, :issue:`8979`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1354
msgid ""
"Quoted command substitution that directly follow a variable expansion (like "
"``echo \"$var$(echo x)\"``) no longer affect the variable expansion (:issue:"
"`8849`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1355
msgid ""
"Fish now correctly expands command substitutions that are preceded by an "
"escaped dollar (like ``echo \\$(echo)``). This regressed in version 3.4.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1356
msgid ""
"``math`` can now handle underscores (``_``) as visual separators in numbers "
"(:issue:`8611`, :issue:`8496`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1358
msgid "math 5 + 2_123_252"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1360
msgid ""
"``math``'s ``min`` and ``max`` functions now take a variable number of "
"arguments instead of always requiring 2 (:issue:`8644`, :issue:`8646`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1362
msgid ""
"> math min 8,2,4\n"
"2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1365
msgid ""
"``read`` is now faster as the last process in a pipeline (:issue:`8552`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1366
msgid ""
"``string join`` gained a new ``--no-empty`` flag to skip empty arguments (:"
"issue:`8774`, :issue:`8351`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1367
msgid ""
"``read`` now only triggers the ``fish_read`` event, not the ``fish_prompt`` "
"event (:issue:`8797`). It was supposed to work this way in fish 3.2.0 and "
"later, but both events were emitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1368
msgid ""
"The TTY modes are no longer restored when non-interactive shells exit. This "
"fixes wrong tty modes in pipelines with interactive commands. (:issue:"
"`8705`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1369
msgid ""
"Some functions shipped with fish printed error messages to standard output, "
"but they now they rightly go to standard error (:issue:`8855`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1370
msgid ""
"``jobs`` now correctly reports CPU usage as a percentage, instead of as a "
"number of clock ticks (:issue:`8919`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1371
msgid ""
"``process-exit`` events now fire when the process exits even if the job has "
"not yet exited, fixing a regression in 3.4.1 (:issue:`8914`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1375
msgid ""
"Fish now reports a special error if a command wasn't found and there is a "
"non-executable file by that name in :envvar:`PATH` (:issue:`8804`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1376
msgid ""
"``less`` and other interactive commands would occasionally be stopped when "
"run in a pipeline with fish functions; this has been fixed (:issue:`8699`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1377
msgid ""
"Case-changing autosuggestions generated mid-token now correctly append only "
"the suffix, instead of duplicating the token (:issue:`8820`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1378
msgid ""
"``ulimit`` learned a number of new options for the resource limits available "
"on Linux, FreeBSD ande NetBSD, and returns a specific warning if the limit "
"specified is not available on the active operating system (:issue:`8823`, :"
"issue:`8786`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1379
msgid ""
"The ``vared`` command can now successfully edit variables named \"tmp\" or "
"\"prompt\" (:issue:`8836`, :issue:`8837`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1380
msgid ""
"``time`` now emits an error if used after the first command in a pipeline (:"
"issue:`8841`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1381
msgid ""
"``fish_add_path`` now prints a message for skipped non-existent paths when "
"using the ``-v`` flag (:issue:`8884`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1382
msgid ""
"Since fish 3.2.0, pressing :kbd:`ctrl-d` while a command is running would "
"end up inserting a space into the next commandline, which has been fixed (:"
"issue:`8871`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1383
msgid ""
"A bug that caused multi-line prompts to be moved down a line when pasting or "
"switching modes has been fixed (:issue:`3481`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1384
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration system no longer strips too many quotes in the "
"abbreviation display (:issue:`8917`, :issue:`8918`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1385
msgid ""
"Fish started with ``--no-config`` will now use the default keybindings (:"
"issue:`8493`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1386
msgid ""
"When fish inherits a :envvar:`USER` environment variable value that doesn't "
"correspond to the current effective user ID, it will now correct it in all "
"cases (:issue:`8879`, :issue:`8583`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1387
msgid ""
"Fish sets a new :envvar:`EUID` variable containing the current effective "
"user id (:issue:`8866`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1388
msgid ""
"``history search`` no longer interprets the search term as an option (:issue:"
"`8853`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1389
msgid ""
"The status message when a job terminates should no longer be erased by a "
"multiline prompt (:issue:`8817`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1393
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`alt-s` binding will now insert ``doas`` instead of ``sudo`` if "
"necessary (:issue:`8942`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1394
msgid ""
"The ``kill-whole-line`` special input function now kills the newline "
"preceding the last line. This makes ``dd`` in vi-mode clear the last line "
"properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1395
msgid ""
"The new ``kill-inner-line`` special input function kills the line without "
"any newlines, allowing ``cc`` in vi-mode to clear the line while preserving "
"newlines (:issue:`8983`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1396
msgid ""
"On terminals that emit special sequences for these combinations, :kbd:`shift-"
"space` is bound like :kbd:`space`, and :kbd:`ctrl-enter` is bound like :kbd:"
"`return` (:issue:`8874`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1400
msgid ""
"A new ``Astronaut`` prompt (:issue:`8775`), a multi-line prompt using plain "
"text reminiscent of the Starship.rs prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1406
msgid "``archlinux-java`` (:issue:`8911`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1407
msgid "``apk`` (:issue:`8951`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1408
msgid "``brightnessctl`` (:issue:`8758`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1409
msgid "``efibootmgr`` (:issue:`9010`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1410
msgid "``fastboot`` (:issue:`8904`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1411
msgid "``optimus-manager`` (:issue:`8913`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1412
msgid "``rclone`` (:issue:`8819`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1413
msgid "``sops`` (:issue:`8821`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1414
msgid "``tuned-adm`` (:issue:`8760`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1415
msgid "``wg-quick`` (:issue:`8687`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1417
msgid ""
"``complete`` can now be given multiple ``--condition`` options. They will be "
"attempted in the order they were given, and only if all succeed will the "
"completion be made available (as if they were connected with ``&&``). This "
"helps with caching - fish's complete system stores the return value of each "
"condition as long as the commandline doesn't change, so this can reduce the "
"number of conditions that need to be evaluated (:issue:`8536`, :issue:"
"`8967`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1421
msgid "Working directory reporting is enabled for kitty (:issue:`8806`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1422
msgid ""
"Changing the cursor shape is now enabled by default in iTerm2 (:issue:"
"`3696`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1426
msgid ""
"libatomic is now correctly detected as necessary when building on RISC-V (:"
"issue:`8850`, :issue:`8851`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1427
msgid ""
"In some cases, the build process found the wrong libintl on macOS. This has "
"been corrected (:issue:`5244`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1428
msgid ""
"The paths for completions, functions, and configuration snippets now include "
"subdirectories ``fish/vendor_completions.d``, ``fish/vendor_functions.d``, "
"and ``fish/vendor_conf.d`` (respectively) within ``XDG_DATA_HOME`` (or ``~/."
"local/share`` if not defined) (:issue:`8887`, :issue:`7816`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1436
msgid "fish 3.4.1 (released March 25, 2022)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1438
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes the following problems identified in fish 3.4.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1440
msgid ""
"An error printed after upgrading, where old instances could pick up a newer "
"version of the ``fish_title`` function, has been fixed (:issue:`8778`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1441
msgid ""
"fish builds correctly on NetBSD (:issue:`8788`) and OpenIndiana (:issue:"
"`8780`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1442
msgid ""
"``nextd-or-forward-word``, bound to :kbd:`alt-right` by default, was "
"inadvertently changed to move like ``forward-bigword``. This has been "
"corrected (:issue:`8790`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1443
msgid ""
"``funcsave -q`` and ``funcsave --quiet`` now work correctly (:issue:`8830`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1444
msgid "Issues with the ``csharp`` and ``nmcli`` completions were corrected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1446
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.3.1 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.4.0 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1451
msgid "fish 3.4.0 (released March 12, 2022)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1455
msgid ""
"fish's command substitution syntax has been extended: ``$(cmd)`` now has the "
"same meaning as ``(cmd)`` but it can be used inside double quotes, to "
"prevent line splitting of the results (:issue:`159`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1457
msgid ""
"foo (bar | string collect)\n"
"# can now be written as\n"
"foo \"$(bar)\"\n"
"\n"
"# and\n"
"\n"
"foo (bar)\n"
"# can now be written as\n"
"foo $(bar)\n"
"# this will still split on newlines only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1468
msgid ""
"Complementing the ``prompt`` command in 3.3.0, ``fish_config`` gained a "
"``theme`` subcommand to show and pick from the sample themes (meaning color "
"schemes) directly in the terminal, instead of having to open a Web browser. "
"For example ``fish_config theme choose Nord`` loads the Nord theme in the "
"current session (:issue:`8132`). The current theme can be saved with "
"``fish_config theme dump``, and custom themes can be added by saving them in "
"``~/.config/fish/themes/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1469
msgid ""
"``set`` and ``read`` learned a new option, ``--function``, to set a variable "
"in the function's top scope. This should be a more familiar way of scoping "
"variables and avoids issues with ``--local``, which is actually block-scoped "
"(:issue:`565`, :issue:`8145`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1471
msgid ""
"function demonstration\n"
"    if true\n"
"        set --function foo bar\n"
"        set --local baz banana\n"
"    end\n"
"    echo $foo # prints \"bar\" because $foo is still valid\n"
"    echo $baz # prints nothing because $baz went out of scope\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1480
msgid ""
"``string pad`` now excludes escape sequences like colors that fish knows "
"about, and a new ``--visible`` flag to ``string length`` makes it use that "
"kind of visible width. This is useful to get the number of terminal cells an "
"already colored string would occupy, like in a prompt. (:issue:`8182`, :"
"issue:`7784`, :issue:`4012`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1482
msgid ""
"> string length --visible (set_color red)foo\n"
"3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1485
msgid ""
"Performance improvements to globbing, especially on systems using glibc. In "
"some cases (large directories with files with many numbers in the names) "
"this almost halves the time taken to expand the glob."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1486
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions can now be turned off by setting "
"``$fish_autosuggestion_enabled`` to 0, and (almost) all highlighting can be "
"turned off by choosing the new \"None\" theme. The exception is necessary "
"colors, like those which distinguish autosuggestions from the actual command "
"line. (:issue:`8376`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1487
msgid ""
"The ``fish_git_prompt`` function, which is included in the default prompts, "
"now overrides ``git`` to avoid running  commands set by per-repository "
"configuration. This avoids a potential security issue in some circumstances, "
"and has been assigned CVE-2022-20001 (:issue:`8589`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1491
msgid ""
"A new feature flag, ``ampersand-nobg-in-token`` makes ``&`` only act as "
"background operator if followed by a separator. In combination with ``qmark-"
"noglob``, this allows entering most URLs at the command line without quoting "
"or escaping (:issue:`7991`). For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1493
msgid ""
"> echo foo&bar # will print \"foo&bar\", instead of running \"echo foo\" in "
"the background and executing \"bar\"\n"
"> echo foo & bar # will still run \"echo foo\" in the background and then "
"run \"bar\"\n"
"# with both ampersand-nobg-in-token and qmark-noglob, this argument has no "
"special characters anymore\n"
"> open https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ&feature=youtu.be"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1498
msgid ""
"As a reminder, feature flags can be set on startup with ``fish --features "
"ampersand-nobg-in-token,qmark-noglob`` or with a universal variable called "
"``fish_features``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1500
msgid "> set -Ua fish_features ampersand-nobg-in-token"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1502
msgid ""
"``$status`` is now forbidden as a command, to prevent a surprisingly common "
"error among new users: Running ``if $status`` (:issue:`8171`). This applies "
"*only* to ``$status``, other variables are still allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1503
msgid ""
"``set --query`` now returns an exit status of 255 if given no variable "
"names. This means ``if set -q $foo`` will not enter the if-block if ``$foo`` "
"is empty or unset. To restore the previous behavior, use ``if not set -q "
"foo; or set -q $foo`` - but this is unlikely to be desirable (:issue:`8214`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1504
msgid "``_`` is now a reserved keyword (:issue:`8342`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1505
msgid ""
"The special input functions ``delete-or-exit``, ``nextd-or-forward-word`` "
"and ``prevd-or-backward-word`` replace fish functions of the same names (:"
"issue:`8538`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1506
msgid ""
"Mac OS X 10.9 is no longer supported. The minimum Mac version is now 10.10 "
"\"Yosemite.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1510
msgid ""
"``string collect`` supports a new ``--allow-empty`` option, which will "
"output one empty argument in a command substitution that has no output (:"
"issue:`8054`). This allows commands like ``test -n (echo -n | string collect "
"--allow-empty)`` to work more reliably. Note this can also be written as "
"``test -n \"$(echo -n)\"`` (see above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1511
msgid ""
"``string match`` gained a ``--groups-only`` option, which makes it only "
"output capturing groups, excluding the full match. This allows ``string "
"match`` to do simple transformations (:issue:`6056`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1513
msgid ""
"> string match -r --groups-only '(.*)fish' 'catfish' 'twofish' 'blue fish' | "
"string escape\n"
"cat\n"
"two\n"
"'blue '"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1518
msgid ""
"``$fish_user_paths`` is now automatically deduplicated to fix a common user "
"error of appending to it in config.fish when it is universal (:issue:"
"`8117`). :doc:`fish_add_path <cmds/fish_add_path>` remains the recommended "
"way to add to $PATH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1519
msgid ""
"``return`` can now be used outside functions. In scripts, it does the same "
"thing as ``exit``. In interactive mode,it sets ``$status`` without exiting (:"
"issue:`8148`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1520
msgid ""
"An oversight prevented all syntax checks from running on commands given to "
"``fish -c`` (:issue:`8171`). This includes checks such as ``exec`` not being "
"allowed in a pipeline, and ``$$`` not being a valid variable. Generally, "
"another error was generated anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1521
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` now correctly reformats tokens that end with a backslash "
"followed by a newline (:issue:`8197`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1522
msgid ""
"``commandline`` gained an ``--is-valid`` option to check if the command line "
"is syntactically valid and complete. This allows basic implementation of "
"transient prompts (:issue:`8142`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1523
msgid ""
"``commandline`` gained a ``--paging-full-mode`` option to check if the pager "
"is showing all the possible lines (no \"7 more rows\" message) (:issue:"
"`8485`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1524
msgid ""
"List expansion correctly reports an error when used with all zero indexes (:"
"issue:`8213`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1525
msgid ""
"Running ``fish`` with a directory instead of a script as argument (eg "
"``fish .``) no longer leads to an infinite loop. Instead it errors out "
"immediately (:issue:`8258`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1526
msgid ""
"Some error messages occurring after fork, like \"text file busy\" have been "
"replaced by bespoke error messages for fish (like \"File is currently open "
"for writing\"). This also restores error messages with current glibc "
"versions that removed sys_errlist (:issue:`8234`, :issue:`4183`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1527
msgid ""
"The ``realpath`` builtin now also squashes leading slashes with the ``--no-"
"symlinks`` option (:issue:`8281`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1528
msgid ""
"When trying to ``cd`` to a dangling (broken) symbolic link, fish will print "
"an error noting that the target is a broken link (:issue:`8264`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1529
msgid ""
"On MacOS terminals that are not granted permissions to access a folder, "
"``cd`` would print a spurious \"rotten symlink\" error, which has been "
"corrected to \"permission denied\" (:issue:`8264`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1530
msgid ""
"Since fish 3.0, ``for`` loops would trigger a variable handler function "
"before the loop was entered. As the variable had not actually changed or "
"been set, this was a spurious event and has been removed (:issue:`8384`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1531
msgid ""
"``math`` now correctly prints negative values and values larger than "
"``2**31`` when in hex or octal bases (:issue:`8417`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1532
msgid ""
"``dirs`` always produces an exit status of 0, instead of sometimes returning "
"1 (:issue:`8211`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1533
msgid "``cd \"\"`` no longer crashes fish (:issue:`8147`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1534
msgid ""
"``set --query`` can now query whether a variable is a path variable via ``--"
"path`` or ``--unpath`` (:issue:`8494`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1535
msgid ""
"Tilde characters (``~``) produced by custom completions are no longer "
"escaped when applied to the command line, making it easier to use the output "
"of a recursive ``complete -C`` in completion scripts (:issue:`4570`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1536
msgid "``set --show`` reports when a variable is read-only (:issue:`8179`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1537
msgid ""
"Erasing ``$fish_emoji_width`` will reset fish to the default guessed emoji "
"width (:issue:`8274`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1538
msgid ""
"The ``la`` function no longer lists entries for \".\" and \"..\", matching "
"other systems defaults (:issue:`8519`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1539
msgid ""
"``abbr -q`` returns the correct exit status when given multiple abbreviation "
"names as arguments (:issue:`8431`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1540
msgid ""
"``command -v`` returns an exit status of 127 instead of 1 if no command was "
"found (:issue:`8547`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1541
msgid ""
"``argparse`` with ``--ignore-unknown`` no longer breaks with multiple "
"unknown options in a short option group (:issue:`8637`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1542
msgid ""
"Comments inside command substitutions or brackets now correctly ignore "
"parentheses, quotes, and brackets (:issue:`7866`, :issue:`8022`, :issue:"
"`8695`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1543
msgid ""
"``complete -C`` supports a new ``--escape`` option, which turns on escaping "
"in returned completion strings (:issue:`3469`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1544
msgid ""
"Invalid byte or unicode escapes like ``\\Utest`` or ``\\xNotHex`` are now a "
"tokenizer error instead of causing the token to be truncated (:issue:`8545`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1548
msgid ""
"Vi mode cursors are now set properly after :kbd:`ctrl-c` (:issue:`8125`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1549
msgid ""
"``funced`` will try to edit the whole file containing a function definition, "
"if there is one (:issue:`391`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1550
msgid ""
"Running a command line consisting of just spaces now deletes an ephemeral "
"(starting with space) history item again (:issue:`8232`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1551
msgid ""
"Command substitutions no longer respect job control, instead running inside "
"fish's own process group (:issue:`8172`). This more closely matches other "
"shells, and improves :kbd:`ctrl-c` reliability inside a command substitution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1552
msgid ""
"``history`` and ``__fish_print_help`` now properly support ``less`` before "
"version 530, including the version that ships with macOS. (:issue:`8157`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1553
msgid ""
"``help`` now knows which section is in which document again (:issue:`8245`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1554
msgid ""
"fish's highlighter will now color options (starting with ``-`` or ``--``) "
"with the color given in the new $fish_color_option, up to the first ``--``. "
"It falls back on $fish_color_param, so nothing changes for existing setups (:"
"issue:`8292`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1555
msgid ""
"When executing a command, abbreviations are no longer expanded when the "
"cursor is separated from the command by spaces, making it easier to suppress "
"abbreviation expansion of commands without arguments. (:issue:`8423`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1556
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader``'s output was simplified. By default, it now only prints "
"a bind statement. The previous per-character timing information can be seen "
"with a new ``--verbose`` switch (:issue:`8467`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1557
msgid ""
"Custom completions are now also loaded for commands that contain tildes or "
"variables like ``~/bin/fish`` or ``$PWD/fish`` (:issue:`8442`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1558
msgid ""
"Command lines spanning multiple lines will not be overwritten by the "
"completion pager when it fills the entire terminal (:issue:`8509`, :issue:"
"`8405`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1559
msgid ""
"When redrawing a multiline prompt, the old prompt is now properly cleared (:"
"issue:`8163`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1560
msgid ""
"Interactive completion would occasionally ignore the last word on the "
"command line due to a race condition. This has been fixed (:issue:`8175`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1561
msgid ""
"Propagation of universal variables from a fish process that is closing is "
"faster (:issue:`8209`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1562
msgid ""
"The command line is drawn in the correct place if the prompt ends with a "
"newline (:issue:`8298`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1563
msgid ""
"``history`` learned a new subcommand ``clear-session`` to erase all history "
"from the current session (:issue:`5791`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1564
msgid ""
"Pressing :kbd:`ctrl-c` in ``fish_key_reader`` will no longer print the "
"incorrect \"Press [ctrl-C] again to exit\" message (:issue:`8510`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1565
msgid ""
"The default command-not-found handler for Fedora/PackageKit now passes the "
"whole command line, allowing for functionality such as running the suggested "
"command directly (:issue:`8579`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1566
msgid ""
"When looking for locale information, the Debian configuration is now used "
"when available (:issue:`8557`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1567
msgid ""
"Pasting text containing quotes from the clipboard trims spaces more "
"appropriately (:issue:`8550`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1568
msgid ""
"The clipboard bindings ignore X-based clipboard programs if the ``DISPLAY`` "
"environment variable is not set, which helps prefer the Windows clipboard "
"when it is available (such as on WSL)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1569
msgid ""
"``funcsave`` will remove a saved copy of a function that has been erased "
"with ``functions --erase``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1570
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration tool gained a number of improvements, including "
"the ability to set pager colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1571
msgid ""
"The default ``fish_title`` prints a shorter title with shortened $PWD and no "
"more redundant \"fish\" (:issue:`8641`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1572
msgid ""
"Holding down an arrow key won't freeze the terminal with long periods of "
"flashing (:issue:`8610`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1573
msgid ""
"Multi-char bindings are no longer interrupted if a signal handler enqueues "
"an event. (:issue:`8628`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1577
msgid ""
":kbd:`escape` can now bound without breaking arrow key bindings (:issue:"
"`8428`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1578
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`alt-h` binding (to open a command’s manual page) now also ignores "
"``command`` (:issue:`8447`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1582
msgid ""
"The ``fish_status_to_signal`` helper function returns the correct signal "
"names for the current platform, rather than Linux (:issue:`8530`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1583
msgid ""
"The ``prompt_pwd`` helper function learned a ``--full-length-dirs N`` option "
"to keep the last N directory components unshortened. In addition the number "
"of characters to shorten each component should be shortened to can now be "
"given as ``-d N`` or ``--dir-length N``. (:issue:`8208`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1585
msgid ""
"> prompt_pwd --full-length-dirs 2 -d 1 ~/dev/fish-shell/share/tools/"
"web_config\n"
"~/d/f/s/tools/web_config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1592
msgid "Apple's ``shortcuts``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1593
msgid "``argparse`` (:issue:`8434`)"
