msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2191
msgid "``traceroute`` and ``tracepath`` (:issue:`6803`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2192
msgid "``windscribe`` (:issue:`6788`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2193
msgid "``wireshark``, ``tshark``, and ``dumpcap``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2194
msgid "``xbps-*`` (:issue:`7239`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2195
msgid ""
"``xxhsum``, ``xxh32sum``, ``xxh64sum`` and ``xxh128sum`` (:issue:`7103`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2196
msgid "``yadm`` (:issue:`7100`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2197
msgid "``zopfli`` and ``zopflipng`` (:issue:`6872`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2199
msgid "Lots of improvements to completions, including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2201
msgid ""
"``git`` completions can complete the right and left parts of a commit range "
"like ``from..to`` or ``left...right``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2202
msgid ""
"Completion scripts for custom Git subcommands like ``git-xyz`` are now "
"loaded with Git completions. The completions can now be defined directly on "
"the subcommand (using ``complete git-xyz``), and completion for ``git xyz`` "
"will work. (:issue:`7075`, :issue:`7652`, :issue:`4358`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2203
msgid ""
"``make`` completions no longer second-guess make's file detection, fixing "
"target completion in some cases (:issue:`7535`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2204
msgid ""
"Command completions now correctly print the description even if the command "
"was fully matched (like in ``ls<TAB>``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2205
msgid ""
"``set`` completions no longer hide variables starting with ``__``, they are "
"sorted last instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2207
msgid ""
"Improvements to the manual page completion generator (:issue:`7086`, :issue:"
"`6879`, :issue:`7187`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2208
msgid ""
"Significant performance improvements to completion of the available commands "
"(:issue:`7153`), especially on macOS Big Sur where there was a significant "
"regression (:issue:`7365`, :issue:`7511`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2209
msgid ""
"Suffix completion using ``__fish_complete_suffix`` uses the same fuzzy "
"matching logic as normal file completion, and completes any file but sorts "
"files with matching suffix first (:issue:`7040`, :issue:`7547`). Previously, "
"it only completed files with matching suffix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2214
msgid ""
"fish has a new interactive test driver based on pexpect, removing the "
"optional dependency on expect (and adding an optional dependency on pexpect) "
"(:issue:`5451`, :issue:`6825`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2215
msgid ""
"The CHANGELOG was moved to restructured text, allowing it to be included in "
"the documentation (:issue:`7057`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2216
msgid ""
"fish handles ncurses installed in a non-standard prefix better (:issue:"
"`6600`, :issue:`7219`), and uses variadic tparm on NetBSD curses (:issue:"
"`6626`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2217
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration tool no longer uses an obsolete Angular version "
"(:issue:`7147`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2218
msgid ""
"The fish project has adopted the Contributor Covenant code of conduct (:"
"issue:`7151`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2223
msgid ""
"The ``fish_color_match`` variable is no longer used. (Previously this "
"controlled the color of matching quotes and parens when using ``read``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2224
msgid ""
"fish 3.2.0 will be the last release in which the redirection to standard "
"error with the ``^`` character is enabled. The ``stderr-nocaret`` feature "
"flag will be changed to \"on\" in future releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2226
msgid ""
"``string`` is now a reserved word and cannot be used for function names (see "
"above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2227
msgid ""
"``fish_vi_cursor``'s option ``--force-iterm`` has been deprecated (see "
"above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2228
msgid ""
"``command``, ``jobs`` and ``type`` long-form option ``--quiet`` is "
"deprecated in favor of ``--query`` (see above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2229
msgid ""
"The ``fish_command_not_found`` event is no longer emitted, instead there is "
"a function of that name. By default it will call a previously-defined "
"``__fish_command_not_found_handler``. To emit the event manually use ``emit "
"fish_command_not_found``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2234
msgid ""
"To disable the greeting message permanently it is no longer enough to just "
"run ``set fish_greeting`` interactively as it is no longer implicitly a "
"universal variable. Use ``set -U fish_greeting`` or disable it in config."
"fish with ``set -g fish_greeting``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2236
msgid ""
"The long-deprecated and non-functional ``-m``/``--read-mode`` options to "
"``read`` were removed in 3.1b1. Using the short form, or a never-implemented "
"``-B`` option, no longer crashes fish (:issue:`7659`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2237
msgid ""
"With the addition of new categories for debug options, the old numbered "
"debugging levels have been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2242
msgid ""
"fish source tarballs are now distributed using the XZ compression method (:"
"issue:`5460`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2244
msgid "The fish source tarball contains an example FreeDesktop entry and icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2245
msgid ""
"The CMake variable ``MAC_CODESIGN_ID`` can now be set to \"off\" to disable "
"code-signing (:issue:`6952`, :issue:`6792`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2246
msgid ""
"Building on on macOS earlier than 10.13.6 succeeds, instead of failing on "
"code-signing (:issue:`6791`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2247
msgid ""
"The pkg-config file now uses variables to ensure paths used are portable "
"across prefixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2248
msgid ""
"The default values for the ``extra_completionsdir``, ``extra_functionsdir`` "
"and ``extra_confdir`` options now use the installation prefix rather than ``/"
"usr/local`` (:issue:`6778`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2250
msgid ""
"A new CMake variable ``FISH_USE_SYSTEM_PCRE2`` controls whether fish builds "
"with the system-installed PCRE2, or the version it bundles. By default it "
"prefers the system library if available, unless Mac codesigning is enabled (:"
"issue:`6952`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2254
msgid ""
"Running the full interactive test suite now requires Python 3.5+ and the "
"pexpect package (:issue:`6825`); the expect package is no longer required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2255
msgid ""
"Support for Python 2 in fish's tools (``fish_config`` and the manual page "
"completion generator) is no longer guaranteed. Please use Python 3.5 or "
"later (:issue:`6537`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2256
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration tool is compatible with Python 3.10  (:issue:"
"`7600`) and no longer requires Python's distutils package (:issue:`7514`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2257
msgid ""
"fish 3.2 is the last release to support Red Hat Enterprise Linux & CentOS "
"version 6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2262
msgid "fish 3.1.2 (released April 29, 2020)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2264
msgid "This release of fish fixes a major issue discovered in fish 3.1.1:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2266
msgid ""
"Commands such as ``fzf`` and ``enhancd``, when used with ``eval``, would "
"hang. ``eval`` buffered output too aggressively, which has been fixed (:"
"issue:`6955`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2270
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.0.0 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.1.1, 3.1.0 and 3.1b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2276
msgid "fish 3.1.1 (released April 27, 2020)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2278
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes a number of major issues discovered in fish 3.1.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2281
msgid ""
"Commands which involve ``. ( ... | psub)`` now work correctly, as a bug in "
"the ``function --on-job-exit`` option has been fixed (:issue:`6613`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2283
msgid ""
"Conflicts between upstream packages for ripgrep and bat, and the fish "
"packages, have been resolved (:issue:`5822`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2285
msgid ""
"Starting fish in a directory without read access, such as via ``su``, no "
"longer crashes (:issue:`6597`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2287
msgid ""
"Glob ordering changes which were introduced in 3.1.0 have been reverted, "
"returning the order of globs to the previous state (:issue:`6593`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2289
msgid ""
"Redirections using the deprecated caret syntax to a file descriptor (eg "
"``^&2``) work correctly (:issue:`6591`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2291
msgid ""
"Redirections that append to a file descriptor (eg ``2>>&1``) work correctly "
"(:issue:`6614`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2293
msgid ""
"Building fish on macOS (:issue:`6602`) or with new versions of GCC (:issue:"
"`6604`, :issue:`6609`) is now successful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2295
msgid ""
"``time`` is now correctly listed in the output of ``builtin -n``, and ``time "
"--help`` works correctly (:issue:`6598`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2297
msgid "Exported universal variables now update properly (:issue:`6612`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2298
msgid ""
"``status current-command`` gives the expected output when used with an "
"environment override - that is, ``F=B status current-command`` returns "
"``status`` instead of ``F=B`` (:issue:`6635`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2301
msgid ""
"``test`` no longer crashes when used with “``nan``” or “``inf``” arguments, "
"erroring out instead (:issue:`6655`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2303
msgid ""
"Copying from the end of the command line no longer crashes fish (:issue:"
"`6680`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2305
msgid ""
"``read`` no longer removes multiple separators when splitting a variable "
"into a list, restoring the previous behaviour from fish 3.0 and before (:"
"issue:`6650`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2308
msgid ""
"Functions using ``--on-job-exit`` and ``--on-process-exit`` work reliably "
"again (:issue:`6679`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2310
msgid ""
"Functions using ``--on-signal INT`` work reliably in interactive sessions, "
"as they did in fish 2.7 and before (:issue:`6649`). These handlers have "
"never worked in non-interactive sessions, and making them work is an ongoing "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2314
msgid ""
"Functions using ``--on-variable`` work reliably with variables which are set "
"implicitly (rather than with ``set``), such as “``fish_bind_mode``” and "
"“``PWD``” (:issue:`6653`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2317
msgid ""
"256 colors are properly enabled under certain conditions that were "
"incorrectly detected in fish 3.1.0 (``$TERM`` begins with xterm, does not "
"include “``256color``”, and ``$TERM_PROGRAM`` is not set) (:issue:`6701`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2321
msgid ""
"The Mercurial (``hg``) prompt no longer produces an error when the current "
"working directory is removed (:issue:`6699`). Also, for performance reasons "
"it shows only basic information by default; to restore the detailed status, "
"set ``$fish_prompt_hg_show_informative_status``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2325
msgid ""
"The VCS prompt, ``fish_vcs_prompt``, no longer displays Subversion (``svn``) "
"status by default, due to the potential slowness of this operation (:issue:"
"`6681`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2328
msgid "Pasting of commands has been sped up (:issue:`6713`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2329
msgid ""
"Using extended Unicode characters, such as emoji, in a non-Unicode capable "
"locale (such as the ``C`` or ``POSIX`` locale) no longer renders all output "
"blank (:issue:`6736`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2332
msgid ""
"``help`` prefers to use ``xdg-open``, avoiding the use of ``open`` on Debian "
"systems where this command is actually ``openvt`` (:issue:`6739`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2334
msgid ""
"Command lines starting with a space, which are not saved in history, now do "
"not get autosuggestions. This fixes an issue with Midnight Commander "
"integration (:issue:`6763`), but may be changed in a future version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2338
msgid ""
"Copying to the clipboard no longer inserts a newline at the end of the "
"content, matching fish 2.7 and earlier (:issue:`6927`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2340
msgid ""
"``fzf`` in complex pipes no longer hangs. More generally, code run as part "
"of command substitutions or ``eval`` will no longer have separate process "
"groups. (:issue:`6624`, :issue:`6806`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2344
msgid "This release also includes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2346
msgid ""
"several changes to improve macOS compatibility with code signing and "
"notarization;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2348
msgid "several improvements to completions; and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2349
msgid "several content and formatting improvements to the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2351
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.0.0 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.1.0 and 3.1b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2355
msgid "Errata for fish 3.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2357
msgid ""
"A new builtin, ``time``, was introduced in the fish 3.1 releases. This "
"builtin is a reserved word (like ``test``, ``function``, and others) because "
"of the way it is implemented, and functions can no longer be named ``time``. "
"This was not clear in the fish 3.1b1 changelog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2365
msgid "fish 3.1.0 (released February 12, 2020)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2367
msgid "Compared to the beta release of fish 3.1b1, fish version 3.1.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2369
msgid ""
"Fixes a regression where spaces after a brace were removed despite brace "
"expansion not occurring (:issue:`6564`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2371
msgid ""
"Fixes a number of problems in compiling and testing on Cygwin (:issue:"
"`6549`) and Solaris-derived systems such as Illumos (:issue:`6553`, :issue:"
"`6554`, :issue:`6555`, :issue:`6556`, and :issue:`6558`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2374
msgid "Fixes the process for building macOS packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2375
msgid ""
"Fixes a regression where excessive error messages are printed if Unicode "
"characters are emitted in non-Unicode-capable locales (:issue:`6584`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2378
msgid ""
"Contains some improvements to the documentation and a small number of "
"completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2381
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.0.0 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.1b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2387
msgid "fish 3.1b1 (released January 26, 2020)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2394
msgid ""
"A new ``$pipestatus`` variable contains a list of exit statuses of the "
"previous job, for each of the separate commands in a pipeline (:issue:"
"`5632`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2397
msgid ""
"fish no longer buffers pipes to the last function in a pipeline, improving "
"many cases where pipes appeared to block or hang (:issue:`1396`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2399
msgid ""
"An overhaul of error messages for builtin commands, including a removal of "
"the overwhelming usage summary, more readable stack traces (:issue:`3404`, :"
"issue:`5434`), and stack traces for ``test`` (aka ``[``) (:issue:`5771`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2402
msgid ""
"fish’s debugging arguments have been significantly improved. The ``--debug-"
"level`` option has been removed, and a new ``--debug`` option replaces it. "
"This option accepts various categories, which may be listed via ``fish --"
"print-debug-categories`` (:issue:`5879`). A new ``--debug-output`` option "
"allows for redirection of debug output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2407
msgid ""
"``string`` has a new ``collect`` subcommand for use in command "
"substitutions, producing a single output instead of splitting on new lines "
"(similar to ``\"$(cmd)\"`` in other shells) (:issue:`159`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2410
msgid ""
"The fish manual, tutorial and FAQ are now available in ``man`` format as "
"``fish-doc``, ``fish-tutorial`` and ``fish-faq`` respectively (:issue:"
"`5521`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2413
msgid ""
"Like other shells, ``cd`` now always looks for its argument in the current "
"directory as a last resort, even if the ``CDPATH`` variable does not include "
"it or “.” (:issue:`4484`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2416
msgid ""
"fish now correctly handles ``CDPATH`` entries that start with ``..`` (:issue:"
"`6220`) or contain ``./`` (:issue:`5887`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2418
msgid ""
"The ``fish_trace`` variable may be set to trace execution (:issue:`3427`). "
"This performs a similar role as ``set -x`` in other shells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2420
msgid ""
"fish uses the temporary directory determined by the system, rather than "
"relying on ``/tmp`` (:issue:`3845`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2422
msgid ""
"The fish Web configuration tool (``fish_config``) prints a list of commands "
"it is executing, to help understanding and debugging (:issue:`5584`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2425
msgid ""
"Major performance improvements when pasting (:issue:`5866`), executing lots "
"of commands (:issue:`5905`), importing history from bash (:issue:`6295`), "
"and when completing variables that might match ``$history`` (:issue:`6288`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2434
msgid ""
"A new builtin command, ``time``, which allows timing of fish functions and "
"builtins as well as external commands (:issue:`117`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2436
msgid ""
"Brace expansion now only takes place if the braces include a “,” or a "
"variable expansion, meaning common commands such as ``git reset HEAD@{0}`` "
"do not require escaping (:issue:`5869`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2439
msgid ""
"New redirections ``&>`` and ``&|`` may be used to redirect or pipe stdout, "
"and also redirect stderr to stdout (:issue:`6192`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2441
msgid ""
"``switch`` now allows arguments that expand to nothing, like empty variables "
"(:issue:`5677`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2443
msgid ""
"The ``VAR=val cmd`` syntax can now be used to run a command in a modified "
"environment (:issue:`6287`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2445
msgid ""
"``and`` is no longer recognised as a command, so that nonsensical constructs "
"like ``and and and`` produce a syntax error (:issue:`6089`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2447
msgid ""
"``math``\\ ‘s exponent operator,’\\ ``^``\\ ‘, was previously left-"
"associative, but now uses the more commonly-used right-associative behaviour "
"(:issue:`6280`). This means that ``math '3^0.5^2'`` was previously "
"calculated as’(3\\ :sup:`0.5)`\\ 2’, but is now calculated as ‘3\\ :sup:"
"`(0.5`\\ 2)’."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2452
msgid ""
"In fish 3.0, the variable used with ``for`` loops inside command "
"substitutions could leak into enclosing scopes; this was an inadvertent "
"behaviour change and has been reverted (:issue:`6480`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2461
msgid "``string split0`` now returns 0 if it split something (:issue:`5701`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2462
msgid ""
"In the interest of consistency, ``builtin -q`` and ``command -q`` can now be "
"used to query if a builtin or command exists (:issue:`5631`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2464
msgid ""
"``math`` now accepts ``--scale=max`` for the maximum scale (:issue:`5579`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2465
msgid ""
"``builtin $var`` now works correctly, allowing a variable as the builtin "
"name (:issue:`5639`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2467
msgid ""
"``cd`` understands the ``--`` argument to make it possible to change to "
"directories starting with a hyphen (:issue:`6071`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2469
msgid "``complete --do-complete`` now also does fuzzy matches (:issue:`5467`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2470
msgid ""
"``complete --do-complete`` can be used inside completions, allowing limited "
"recursion (:issue:`3474`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2472
msgid "``count`` now also counts lines fed on standard input (:issue:`5744`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2473
msgid ""
"``eval`` produces an exit status of 0 when given no arguments, like other "
"shells (:issue:`5692`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2475
msgid ""
"``printf`` prints what it can when input hasn’t been fully converted to a "
"number, but still prints an error (:issue:`5532`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2477
msgid ""
"``complete -C foo`` now works as expected, rather than requiring ``complete -"
"Cfoo``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2479
msgid ""
"``complete`` has a new ``--force-files`` option, to re-enable file "
"completions. This allows ``sudo -E`` and ``pacman -Qo`` to complete "
"correctly (:issue:`5646`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2482
msgid ""
"``argparse`` now defaults to showing the current function name (instead of "
"``argparse``) in its errors, making ``--name`` often superfluous (:issue:"
"`5835`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2485
msgid ""
"``argparse`` has a new ``--ignore-unknown`` option to keep unrecognized "
"options, allowing multiple argparse passes to parse options (:issue:`5367`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2488
msgid ""
"``argparse`` correctly handles flag value validation of options that only "
"have short names (:issue:`5864`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2490
msgid ""
"``read -S`` (short option of ``--shell``) is recognised correctly (:issue:"
"`5660`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2492
msgid ""
"``read`` understands ``--list``, which acts like ``--array`` in reading all "
"arguments into a list inside a single variable, but is better named (:issue:"
"`5846`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2495
msgid ""
"``read`` has a new option, ``--tokenize``, which splits a string into "
"variables according to the shell’s tokenization rules, considering quoting, "
"escaping, and so on (:issue:`3823`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2498
msgid ""
"``read`` interacts more correctly with the deprecated ``$IFS`` variable, in "
"particular removing multiple separators when splitting a variable into a "
"list (:issue:`6406`), matching other shells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2501
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` now handles semicolons better, including leaving them in "
"place for ``; and`` and ``; or`` instead of breaking the line (:issue:"
"`5859`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2504
msgid ""
"``fish_indent --write`` now supports multiple file arguments, indenting them "
"in turn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2506
msgid "The default read limit has been increased to 100MiB (:issue:`5267`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2507
msgid ""
"``math`` now also understands ``x`` for multiplication, provided it is "
"followed by whitespace (:issue:`5906`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2509
msgid ""
"``math`` reports the right error when incorrect syntax is used inside "
"parentheses (:issue:`6063`), and warns when unsupported logical operations "
"are used (:issue:`6096`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2512
msgid ""
"``functions --erase`` now also prevents fish from autoloading a function for "
"the first time (:issue:`5951`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2514
msgid ""
"``jobs --last`` returns 0 to indicate success when a job is found (:issue:"
"`6104`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2516
msgid ""
"``commandline -p`` and ``commandline -j`` now split on ``&&`` and ``||`` in "
"addition to ``;`` and ``&`` (:issue:`6214`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2518
msgid ""
"A bug where ``string split`` would drop empty strings if the output was only "
"empty strings has been fixed (:issue:`5987`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2520
msgid ""
"``eval`` no long creates a new local variable scope, but affects variables "
"in the scope it is called from (:issue:`4443`). ``source`` still creates a "
"new local scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2523
msgid ""
"``abbr`` has a new ``--query`` option to check for the existence of an "
"abbreviation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2525
msgid ""
"Local values for ``fish_complete_path`` and ``fish_function_path`` are now "
"ignored; only their global values are respected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2527
msgid ""
"Syntax error reports now display a marker in the correct position (:issue:"
"`5812`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2529
msgid "Empty universal variables may now be exported (:issue:`5992`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2530
msgid ""
"Exported universal variables are no longer imported into the global scope, "
"preventing shadowing. This makes it easier to change such variables for all "
"fish sessions and avoids breakage when the value is a list of multiple "
"elements (:issue:`5258`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2534
msgid ""
"A bug where ``for`` could use invalid variable names has been fixed (:issue:"
"`5800`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2536
msgid ""
"A bug where local variables would not be exported to functions has been "
"fixed (:issue:`6153`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2538
msgid ""
"The null command (``:``) now always exits successfully, rather than passing "
"through the previous exit status (:issue:`6022`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2540
msgid ""
"The output of ``functions FUNCTION`` matches the declaration of the "
"function, correctly including comments or blank lines (:issue:`5285`), and "
"correctly includes any ``--wraps`` flags (:issue:`1625`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2543
msgid ""
"``type`` supports a new option, ``--short``, which suppress function "
"expansion (:issue:`6403`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2545
msgid ""
"``type --path`` with a function argument will now output the path to the "
"file containing the definition of that function, if it exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2547
msgid ""
"``type --force-path`` with an argument that cannot be found now correctly "
"outputs nothing, as documented (:issue:`6411`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2549
msgid ""
"The ``$hostname`` variable is no longer truncated to 32 characters (:issue:"
"`5758`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2551
msgid ""
"Line numbers in function backtraces are calculated correctly (:issue:`6350`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2552
msgid ""
"A new ``fish_cancel`` event is emitted when the command line is cancelled, "
"which is useful for terminal integration (:issue:`5973`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2560
msgid ""
"New Base16 color options are available through the Web-based configuration (:"
"issue:`6504`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2562
msgid ""
"fish only parses ``/etc/paths`` on macOS in login shells, matching the bash "
"implementation (:issue:`5637`) and avoiding changes to path ordering in "
"child shells (:issue:`5456`). It now ignores blank lines like the bash "
"implementation (:issue:`5809`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2566
msgid ""
"The locale is now reloaded when the ``LOCPATH`` variable is changed (:issue:"
"`5815`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2568
msgid ""
"``read`` no longer keeps a history, making it suitable for operations that "
"shouldn’t end up there, like password entry (:issue:`5904`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2570
msgid ""
"``dirh`` outputs its stack in the correct order (:issue:`5477`), and behaves "
"as documented when universal variables are used for its stack (:issue:"
"`5797`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2573
msgid ""
"``funced`` and the edit-commandline-in-buffer bindings did not work in fish "
"3.0 when the ``$EDITOR`` variable contained spaces; this has been corrected "
"(:issue:`5625`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2576
msgid ""
"Builtins now pipe their help output to a pager automatically (:issue:`6227`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2577
msgid ""
"``set_color`` now colors the ``--print-colors`` output in the matching "
"colors if it is going to a terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2579
msgid ""
"fish now underlines every valid entered path instead of just the last one (:"
"issue:`5872`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2581
msgid ""
"When syntax highlighting a string with an unclosed quote, only the quote "
"itself will be shown as an error, instead of the whole argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2584
msgid ""
"Syntax highlighting works correctly with variables as commands (:issue:"
"`5658`) and redirections to close file descriptors (:issue:`6092`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2586
msgid ""
"``help`` works properly on Windows Subsystem for Linux (:issue:`5759`, :"
"issue:`6338`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2587
msgid ""
"A bug where ``disown`` could crash the shell has been fixed (:issue:`5720`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2588
msgid ""
"fish will not autosuggest files ending with ``~`` unless there are no other "
"candidates, as these are generally backup files (:issue:`985`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2590
msgid "Escape in the pager works correctly (:issue:`5818`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2591
msgid ""
"Key bindings that call ``fg`` no longer leave the terminal in a broken state "
"(:issue:`2114`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2593
msgid ""
"Brackets (:issue:`5831`) and filenames containing ``$`` (:issue:`6060`) are "
"completed with appropriate escaping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2595
msgid ""
"The output of ``complete`` and ``functions`` is now colorized in interactive "
"terminals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2597
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration handles aliases that include single quotes "
"correctly (:issue:`6120`), and launches correctly under Termux (:issue:"
"`6248`) and OpenBSD (:issue:`6522`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2600
msgid ""
"``function`` now correctly validates parameters for ``--argument-names`` as "
"valid variable names (:issue:`6147`) and correctly parses options following "
"``--argument-names``, as in “``--argument-names foo --description bar``” (:"
"issue:`6186`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2604
msgid ""
"History newly imported from bash includes command lines using ``&&`` or ``||"
"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2606
msgid ""
"The automatic generation of completions from manual pages is better "
"described in job and process listings, and no longer produces a warning when "
"exiting fish (:issue:`6269`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2609
msgid ""
"In private mode, setting ``$fish_greeting`` to an empty string before "
"starting the private session will prevent the warning about history not "
"being saved from being printed (:issue:`6299`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2612
msgid ""
"In the interactive editor, a line break (Enter) inside unclosed brackets "
"will insert a new line, rather than executing the command and producing an "
"error (:issue:`6316`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2615
msgid "Ctrl-C always repaints the prompt (:issue:`6394`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2616
msgid ""
"When run interactively from another program (such as Python), fish will "
"correctly start a new process group, like other shells (:issue:`5909`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2618
msgid ""
"Job identifiers (for example, for background jobs) are assigned more "
"logically (:issue:`6053`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2620
msgid ""
"A bug where history would appear truncated if an empty command was executed "
"was fixed (:issue:`6032`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2628
msgid ""
"Pasting strips leading spaces to avoid pasted commands being omitted from "
"the history (:issue:`4327`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2630
msgid ""
"Shift-Left and Shift-Right now default to moving backwards and forwards by "
"one bigword (words separated by whitespace) (:issue:`1505`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2632
msgid ""
"The default escape delay (to differentiate between the escape key and an alt-"
"combination) has been reduced to 30ms, down from 300ms for the default mode "
"and 100ms for Vi mode (:issue:`3904`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2635
msgid ""
"The ``forward-bigword`` binding now interacts correctly with autosuggestions "
"(:issue:`5336`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2637
msgid ""
"The ``fish_clipboard_*`` functions support Wayland by using `wl-clipboard "
"<https://github.com/bugaevc/wl-clipboard>`_ (:issue:`5450`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2640
msgid ""
"The ``nextd`` and ``prevd`` functions no longer print “Hit end of history”, "
"instead using a bell. They correctly store working directories containing "
"symbolic links (:issue:`6395`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2643
msgid ""
"If a ``fish_mode_prompt`` function exists, Vi mode will only execute it on "
"mode-switch instead of the entire prompt. This should make it much more "
"responsive with slow prompts (:issue:`5783`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2646
msgid ""
"The path-component bindings (like Ctrl-w) now also stop at “:” and “@”, "
"because those are used to denote user and host in commands such as ``ssh`` (:"
"issue:`5841`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2649
msgid ""
"The NULL character can now be bound via ``bind -k nul``. Terminals often "
"generate this character via control-space. (:issue:`3189`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2651
msgid ""
"A new readline command ``expand-abbr`` can be used to trigger abbreviation "
"expansion (:issue:`5762`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2653
msgid ""
"A new readline command, ``delete-or-exit``, removes a character to the right "
"of the cursor or exits the shell if the command line is empty (moving this "
"functionality out of the ``delete-or-exit`` function)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2657
msgid ""
"The ``self-insert`` readline command will now insert the binding sequence, "
"if not empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2659
msgid ""
"A new binding to prepend ``sudo``, bound to Alt-S by default (:issue:`6140`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2660
msgid ""
"The Alt-W binding to describe a command should now work better with "
"multiline prompts (:issue:`6110`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2662
msgid ""
"The Alt-H binding to open a command’s man page now tries to ignore ``sudo`` "
"(:issue:`6122`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2664
msgid ""
"A new pair of bind functions, ``history-prefix-search-backward`` (and "
"``forward``), was introduced (:issue:`6143`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2666
msgid ""
"Vi mode now supports R to enter replace mode (:issue:`6342`), and ``d0`` to "
"delete the current line (:issue:`6292`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2668
msgid ""
"In Vi mode, hitting Enter in replace-one mode no longer erases the prompt (:"
"issue:`6298`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2670
msgid ""
"Selections in Vi mode are inclusive, matching the actual behaviour of Vi (:"
"issue:`5770`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2678
msgid ""
"The Git prompt in informative mode now shows the number of stashes if "
"enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2680
msgid ""
"The Git prompt now has an option "
"(``$__fish_git_prompt_use_informative_chars``) to use the (more modern) "
"informative characters without enabling informative mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2683
msgid ""
"The default prompt now also features VCS integration and will color the host "
"if running via SSH (:issue:`6375`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2685
msgid ""
"The default and example prompts print the pipe status if an earlier command "
"in the pipe fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2687
msgid ""
"The default and example prompts try to resolve exit statuses to signal names "
"when appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2693
msgid "Improved terminal output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2695
msgid ""
"New ``fish_pager_color_`` options have been added to control more elements "
"of the pager’s colors (:issue:`5524`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2697
msgid ""
"Better detection and support for using fish from various system consoles, "
"where limited colors and special characters are supported (:issue:`5552`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2700
msgid ""
"fish now tries to guess if the system supports Unicode 9 (and displays emoji "
"as wide), eliminating the need to set ``$fish_emoji_width`` in most cases (:"
"issue:`5722`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2703
msgid ""
"Improvements to the display of wide characters, particularly Korean "
"characters and emoji (:issue:`5583`, :issue:`5729`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2705
msgid ""
"The Vi mode cursor is correctly redrawn when regaining focus under terminals "
"that report focus (eg tmux) (:issue:`4788`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2707
msgid ""
"Variables that control background colors (such as "
"``fish_pager_color_search_match``) can now use ``--reverse``."
msgstr ""

