#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2768 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3396
msgid "Lots of improvements to completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2769
msgid ""
"Selecting short options which also have a long name from the completion "
"pager is possible (:issue:`5634`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2771
msgid ""
"Tab completion will no longer add trailing spaces if they already exist (:"
"issue:`6107`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2773
msgid ""
"Completion of subcommands to builtins like ``and`` or ``not`` now works "
"correctly (:issue:`6249`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2775
msgid ""
"Completion of arguments to short options works correctly when multiple short "
"options are used together (:issue:`332`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2777
msgid ""
"Activating completion in the middle of an invalid completion does not move "
"the cursor any more, making it easier to fix a mistake (:issue:`4124`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2779
msgid "Completion in empty commandlines now lists all available commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2780
msgid ""
"Functions listed as completions could previously leak parts of the function "
"as other completions; this has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2788
msgid ""
"The vcs-prompt functions have been promoted to names without double-"
"underscore, so \\__fish_git_prompt is now fish_git_prompt, "
"\\__fish_vcs_prompt is now fish_vcs_prompt, \\__fish_hg_prompt is now "
"fish_hg_prompt and \\__fish_svn_prompt is now fish_svn_prompt. Shims at the "
"old names have been added, and the variables have kept their old names (:"
"issue:`5586`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2794
msgid ""
"``string replace`` has an additional round of escaping in the replacement "
"expression, so escaping backslashes requires many escapes (eg ``string "
"replace -ra '([ab])' '\\\\\\\\\\\\\\$1' a``). The new feature flag ``regex-"
"easyesc`` can be used to disable this, so that the same effect can be "
"achieved with ``string replace -ra '([ab])' '\\\\\\\\$1' a`` (:issue:"
"`5556`). As a reminder, the intention behind feature flags is that this will "
"eventually become the default and then only option, so scripts should be "
"updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2803
msgid ""
"The ``fish_vi_mode`` function, deprecated in fish 2.3, has been removed. Use "
"``fish_vi_key_bindings`` instead (:issue:`6372`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2811
msgid ""
"fish 3.0 introduced a CMake-based build system. In fish 3.1, both the "
"Autotools-based build and legacy Xcode build system have been removed, "
"leaving only the CMake build system. All distributors and developers must "
"install CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2815
msgid ""
"fish now depends on the common ``tee`` external command, for the ``psub`` "
"process substitution function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2817
msgid ""
"The documentation is now built with Sphinx. The old Doxygen-based "
"documentation system has been removed. Developers, and distributors who wish "
"to rebuild the documentation, must install Sphinx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2820
msgid ""
"The ``INTERNAL_WCWIDTH`` build option has been removed, as fish now always "
"uses an internal ``wcwidth`` function. It has a number of configuration "
"options that make it more suitable for general use (:issue:`5777`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2824
msgid ""
"mandoc can now be used to format the output from ``--help`` if ``nroff`` is "
"not installed, reducing the number of external dependencies on systems with "
"``mandoc`` installed (:issue:`5489`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2827
msgid ""
"Some bugs preventing building on Solaris-derived systems such as Illumos "
"were fixed (:issue:`5458`, :issue:`5461`, :issue:`5611`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2829
msgid ""
"Completions for ``npm``, ``bower`` and ``yarn`` no longer require the ``jq`` "
"utility for full functionality, but will use Python instead if it is "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2832
msgid ""
"The paths for completions, functions and configuration snippets have been "
"extended. On systems that define ``XDG_DATA_DIRS``, each of the directories "
"in this variable are searched in the subdirectories ``fish/"
"vendor_completions.d``, ``fish/vendor_functions.d``, and ``fish/vendor_conf."
"d`` respectively. On systems that do not define this variable in the "
"environment, the vendor directories are searched for in both the "
"installation prefix and the default “extra” directory, which now defaults to "
"``/usr/local`` (:issue:`5029`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2844
msgid "fish 3.0.2 (released February 19, 2019)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2846
msgid "This release of fish fixes an issue discovered in fish 3.0.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2849 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2868
msgid "Fixes and improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2851
msgid ""
"The PWD environment variable is now ignored if it does not resolve to the "
"true working directory, fixing strange behaviour in terminals started by "
"editors and IDEs (:issue:`5647`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2855
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 2.7.1 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.0.1, 3.0.0 and 3.0b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2860
msgid "fish 3.0.1 (released February 11, 2019)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2862
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes a number of major issues discovered in fish 3.0.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2870
msgid ""
"``exec`` does not complain about running foreground jobs when called (:issue:"
"`5449`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2872
msgid ""
"while loops now evaluate to the last executed command in the loop body (or "
"zero if the body was empty), matching POSIX semantics (:issue:`4982`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2875
msgid ""
"``read --silent`` no longer echoes to the tty when run from a non-"
"interactive script (:issue:`5519`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2877
msgid ""
"On macOS, path entries with spaces in ``/etc/paths`` and ``/etc/paths.d`` "
"now correctly set path entries with spaces. Likewise, ``MANPATH`` is "
"correctly set from ``/etc/manpaths`` and ``/etc/manpaths.d`` (:issue:`5481`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2881
msgid "fish starts correctly under Cygwin/MSYS2 (:issue:`5426`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2882
msgid ""
"The ``pager-toggle-search`` binding (Ctrl-S by default) will now activate "
"the search field, even when the pager is not focused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2884
msgid ""
"The error when a command is not found is now printed a single time, instead "
"of once per argument (:issue:`5588`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2886
msgid ""
"Fixes and improvements to the git completions, including printing correct "
"paths with older git versions, fuzzy matching again, reducing unnecessary "
"offers of root paths (starting with ``:/``) (:issue:`5578`, :issue:`5574`, :"
"issue:`5476`), and ignoring shell aliases, so enterprising users can set up "
"the wrapping command (via ``set -g __fish_git_alias_$command $whatitwraps``) "
"(:issue:`5412`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2892
msgid ""
"Significant performance improvements to core shell functions (:issue:`5447`) "
"and to the ``kill`` completions (:issue:`5541`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2894
msgid ""
"Starting in symbolically-linked working directories works correctly (:issue:"
"`5525`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2896
msgid ""
"The default ``fish_title`` function no longer contains extra spaces (:issue:"
"`5517`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2898
msgid ""
"The ``nim`` prompt now works correctly when chosen in the Web-based "
"configuration (:issue:`5490`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2900
msgid ""
"``string`` now prints help to stdout, like other builtins (:issue:`5495`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2901
msgid ""
"Killing the terminal while fish is in vi normal mode will no longer send it "
"spinning and eating CPU. (:issue:`5528`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2903
msgid ""
"A number of crashes have been fixed (:issue:`5550`, :issue:`5548`, :issue:"
"`5479`, :issue:`5453`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2904
msgid "Improvements to the documentation and certain completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2907 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3440
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3917
msgid "Known issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2909
msgid ""
"There is one significant known issue that was not corrected before the "
"release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2912
msgid ""
"fish does not run correctly under Windows Services for Linux before Windows "
"10 version 1809/17763, and the message warning of this may not be displayed "
"(:issue:`5619`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2916
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 2.7.1 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.0.0 and 3.0b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2922
msgid "fish 3.0.0 (released December 28, 2018)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2924
msgid ""
"fish 3 is a major release, which introduces some breaking changes alongside "
"improved functionality. Although most existing scripts will continue to "
"work, they should be reviewed against the list contained in the 3.0b1 "
"release notes below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2929
msgid "Compared to the beta release of fish 3.0b1, fish version 3.0.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2931
msgid "builds correctly against musl libc (:issue:`5407`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2932
msgid "handles huge numeric arguments to ``test`` correctly (:issue:`5414`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2933
msgid ""
"removes the history colouring introduced in 3.0b1, which did not always work "
"correctly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2936
msgid ""
"There is one significant known issue which was not able to be corrected "
"before the release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2939
msgid ""
"fish 3.0.0 builds on Cygwin (:issue:`5423`), but does not run correctly (:"
"issue:`5426`) and will result in a hanging terminal when started. Cygwin "
"users are encouraged to continue using 2.7.1 until a release which corrects "
"this is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2944
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 2.7.1 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.0b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2950
msgid "fish 3.0b1 (released December 11, 2018)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2952
msgid ""
"fish 3 is a major release, which introduces some breaking changes alongside "
"improved functionality. Although most existing scripts will continue to "
"work, they should be reviewed against the list below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2957
msgid "Notable non-backward compatible changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2959
msgid ""
"Process and job expansion has largely been removed. ``%`` will no longer "
"perform these expansions, except for ``%self`` for the PID of the current "
"shell. Additionally, job management commands (``disown``, ``wait``, ``bg``, "
"``fg`` and ``kill``) will expand job specifiers starting with ``%`` (:issue:"
"`4230`, :issue:`1202`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2964
msgid ""
"``set x[1] x[2] a b``, to set multiple elements of an array at once, is no "
"longer valid syntax (:issue:`4236`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2966
msgid ""
"A literal ``{}`` now expands to itself, rather than nothing. This makes "
"working with ``find -exec`` easier (:issue:`1109`, :issue:`4632`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2968
msgid ""
"Literally accessing a zero-index is now illegal syntax and is caught by the "
"parser (:issue:`4862`). (fish indices start at 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2970
msgid ""
"Successive commas in brace expansions are handled in less surprising manner. "
"For example, ``{,,,}`` expands to four empty strings rather than an empty "
"string, a comma and an empty string again (:issue:`3002`, :issue:`4632`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2974
msgid ""
"``for`` loop control variables are no longer local to the ``for`` block (:"
"issue:`1935`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2976
msgid ""
"Variables set in ``if`` and ``while`` conditions are available outside the "
"block (:issue:`4820`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2978
msgid ""
"Local exported (``set -lx``) vars are now visible to functions (:issue:"
"`1091`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2980
msgid ""
"The new ``math`` builtin (see below) does not support logical expressions; "
"``test`` should be used instead (:issue:`4777`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2982
msgid ""
"Range expansion will now behave sensibly when given a single positive and "
"negative index (``$foo[5..-1]`` or ``$foo[-1..5]``), clamping to the last "
"valid index without changing direction if the list has fewer elements than "
"expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2986
msgid ""
"``read`` now uses ``-s`` as short for ``--silent`` (à la ``bash``); ``--"
"shell``\\ ’s abbreviation (formerly ``-s``) is now ``-S`` instead (:issue:"
"`4490`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2989
msgid ""
"``cd`` no longer resolves symlinks. fish now maintains a virtual path, "
"matching other shells (:issue:`3350`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2991
msgid ""
"``source`` now requires an explicit ``-`` as the filename to read from the "
"terminal (:issue:`2633`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2993
msgid "Arguments to ``end`` are now errors, instead of being silently ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2995
msgid ""
"The names ``argparse``, ``read``, ``set``, ``status``, ``test`` and ``[`` "
"are now reserved and not allowed as function names. This prevents users "
"unintentionally breaking stuff (:issue:`3000`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2998
msgid ""
"The ``fish_user_abbreviations`` variable is no longer used; abbreviations "
"will be migrated to the new storage format automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3001
msgid ""
"The ``FISH_READ_BYTE_LIMIT`` variable is now called ``fish_byte_limit`` (:"
"issue:`4414`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3003
msgid ""
"Environment variables are no longer split into arrays based on the record "
"separator character on startup. Instead, variables are not split, unless "
"their name ends in PATH, in which case they are split on colons (:issue:"
"`436`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3007
msgid ""
"The ``history`` builtin’s ``--with-time`` option has been removed; this has "
"been deprecated in favor of ``--show-time`` since 2.7.0 (:issue:`4403`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3010
msgid ""
"The internal variables ``__fish_datadir`` and ``__fish_sysconfdir`` are now "
"known as ``__fish_data_dir`` and ``__fish_sysconf_dir`` respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3015
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3017
msgid ""
"With the release of fish 3, a number of features have been marked for "
"removal in the future. All users are encouraged to explore alternatives. A "
"small number of these features are currently behind feature flags, which are "
"turned on at present but may be turned off by default in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3023
msgid ""
"A new feature flags mechanism is added for staging deprecations and breaking "
"changes. Feature flags may be specified at launch with ``fish --features ..."
"`` or by setting the universal ``fish_features`` variable. (:issue:`4940`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3028
msgid ""
"The use of the ``IFS`` variable for ``read`` is deprecated; ``IFS`` will be "
"ignored in the future (:issue:`4156`). Use the ``read --delimiter`` option "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3031
msgid ""
"The ``function --on-process-exit`` switch will be removed in future (:issue:"
"`4700`). Use the ``fish_exit`` event instead: ``function --on-event "
"fish_exit``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3034
msgid ""
"``$_`` is deprecated and will removed in the future (:issue:`813`). Use "
"``status current-command`` in a command substitution instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3036
msgid ""
"``^`` as a redirection deprecated and will be removed in the future. (:issue:"
"`4394`). Use ``2>`` to redirect stderr. This is controlled by the ``stderr-"
"nocaret`` feature flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3039
msgid ""
"``?`` as a glob (wildcard) is deprecated and will be removed in the future (:"
"issue:`4520`). This is controlled by the ``qmark-noglob`` feature flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3044 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3460
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3582 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3678
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3746 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3795
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3877
msgid "Notable fixes and improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3051
msgid ""
"fish now supports ``&&`` (like ``and``), ``||`` (like ``or``), and ``!`` "
"(like ``not``), for better migration from POSIX-compliant shells (:issue:"
"`4620`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3054
msgid "Variables may be used as commands (:issue:`154`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3055
msgid ""
"fish may be started in private mode via ``fish --private``. Private mode "
"fish sessions do not have access to the history file and any commands "
"evaluated in private mode are not persisted for future sessions. A session "
"variable ``$fish_private_mode`` can be queried to detect private mode and "
"adjust the behavior of scripts accordingly to respect the user’s wish for "
"privacy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3061
msgid ""
"A new ``wait`` command for waiting on backgrounded processes (:issue:`4498`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3062
msgid ""
"``math`` is now a builtin rather than a wrapper around ``bc`` (:issue:"
"`3157`). Floating point computations is now used by default, and can be "
"controlled with the new ``--scale`` option (:issue:`4478`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3065
msgid ""
"Setting ``$PATH`` no longer warns on non-existent directories, allowing for "
"a single $PATH to be shared across machines (eg via dotfiles) (:issue:"
"`2969`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3068
msgid ""
"``while`` sets ``$status`` to a non-zero value if the loop is not executed (:"
"issue:`4982`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3070
msgid ""
"Command substitution output is now limited to 10 MB by default, controlled "
"by the ``fish_read_limit`` variable (:issue:`3822`). Notably, this is larger "
"than most operating systems’ argument size limit, so trying to pass argument "
"lists this size to external commands has never worked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3075
msgid ""
"The machine hostname, where available, is now exposed as the ``$hostname`` "
"reserved variable. This removes the dependency on the ``hostname`` "
"executable (:issue:`4422`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3078
msgid ""
"Bare ``bind`` invocations in config.fish now work. The "
"``fish_user_key_bindings`` function is no longer necessary, but will still "
"be executed if it exists (:issue:`5191`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3081
msgid ""
"``$fish_pid`` and ``$last_pid`` are available as replacements for ``%self`` "
"and ``%last``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3085
msgid "New features in commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3087
msgid ""
"``alias`` has a new ``--save`` option to save the generated function "
"immediately (:issue:`4878`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3089
msgid ""
"``bind`` has a new ``--silent`` option to ignore bind requests for named "
"keys not available under the current terminal (:issue:`4188`, :issue:`4431`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3091
msgid ""
"``complete`` has a new ``--keep-order`` option to show the provided or "
"dynamically-generated argument list in the same order as specified, rather "
"than alphabetically (:issue:`361`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3094
msgid "``exec`` prompts for confirmation if background jobs are running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3095
msgid ""
"``funced`` has a new ``--save`` option to automatically save the edited "
"function after successfully editing (:issue:`4668`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3097
msgid ""
"``functions`` has a new ``--handlers`` option to show functions registered "
"as event handlers (:issue:`4694`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3099
msgid ""
"``history search`` supports globs for wildcard searching (:issue:`3136`) and "
"has a new ``--reverse`` option to show entries from oldest to newest (:issue:"
"`4375`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3102
msgid "``jobs`` has a new ``--quiet`` option to silence the output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3103
msgid ""
"``read`` has a new ``--delimiter`` option for splitting input into arrays (:"
"issue:`4256`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3105
msgid ""
"``read`` writes directly to stdout if called without arguments (:issue:"
"`4407`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3107
msgid ""
"``read`` can now read individual lines into separate variables without "
"consuming the input in its entirety via the new ``/--line`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3110
msgid "``set`` has new ``--append`` and ``--prepend`` options (:issue:`1326`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3111
msgid ""
"``string match`` with an empty pattern and ``--entire`` in glob mode now "
"matches everything instead of nothing (:issue:`4971`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3113
msgid ""
"``string split`` supports a new ``--no-empty`` option to exclude empty "
"strings from the result (:issue:`4779`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3115
msgid ""
"``string`` has new subcommands ``split0`` and ``join0`` for working with NUL-"
"delimited output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3117
msgid ""
"``string`` no longer stops processing text after NUL characters (:issue:"
"`4605`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3119
msgid ""
"``string escape`` has a new ``--style regex`` option for escaping strings to "
"be matched literally in ``string`` regex operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3121
msgid "``test`` now supports floating point values in numeric comparisons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3128
msgid ""
"A pipe at the end of a line now allows the job to continue on the next line "
"(:issue:`1285`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3130
msgid ""
"Italics and dim support out of the box on macOS for Terminal.app and iTerm (:"
"issue:`4436`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3132
msgid ""
"``cd`` tab completions no longer descend into the deepest unambiguous path (:"
"issue:`4649`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3134
msgid ""
"Pager navigation has been improved. Most notably, moving down now wraps "
"around, moving up from the commandline now jumps to the last element and "
"moving right and left now reverse each other even when wrapping around (:"
"issue:`4680`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3138
msgid ""
"Typing normal characters while the completion pager is active no longer "
"shows the search field. Instead it enters them into the command line, and "
"ends paging (:issue:`2249`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3141
msgid ""
"A new input binding ``pager-toggle-search`` toggles the search field in the "
"completions pager on and off. By default, this is bound to Ctrl-S."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3144
msgid "Searching in the pager now does a full fuzzy search (:issue:`5213`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3145
msgid ""
"The pager will now show the full command instead of just its last line if "
"the number of completions is large (:issue:`4702`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3147
msgid "Abbreviations can be tab-completed (:issue:`3233`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3148
msgid ""
"Tildes in file names are now properly escaped in completions (:issue:`2274`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3149
msgid ""
"Wrapping completions (from ``complete --wraps`` or ``function --wraps``) can "
"now inject arguments. For example, ``complete gco --wraps 'git checkout'`` "
"now works properly (:issue:`1976`). The ``alias`` function has been updated "
"to respect this behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3153
msgid ""
"Path completions now support expansions, meaning expressions like ``python ~/"
"<TAB>`` now provides file suggestions just like any other relative or "
"absolute path. (This includes support for other expansions, too.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3157
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions try to avoid arguments that are already present in the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3159
msgid ""
"Notifications about crashed processes are now always shown, even in command "
"substitutions (:issue:`4962`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3161
msgid ""
"The screen is no longer reset after a BEL, fixing graphical glitches (:issue:"
"`3693`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3163
msgid ""
"vi-mode now supports ‘;’ and ‘,’ motions. This introduces new {forward,"
"backward}-jump-till and repeat-jump{,-reverse} bind functions (:issue:"
"`5140`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3166
msgid "The ``*y`` vi-mode binding now works (:issue:`5100`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3167
msgid "True color is now enabled in neovim by default (:issue:`2792`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3168
msgid ""
"Terminal size variables (``$COLUMNS``/``$LINES``) are now updated before "
"``fish_prompt`` is called, allowing the prompt to react (:issue:`904`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3171
msgid ""
"Multi-line prompts no longer repeat when the terminal is resized (:issue:"
"`2320`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3173
msgid ""
"``xclip`` support has been added to the clipboard integration (:issue:"
"`5020`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3175
msgid ""
"The Alt-P keybinding paginates the last command if the command line is empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3177
msgid ""
"``$cmd_duration`` is no longer reset when no command is executed (:issue:"
"`5011`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3179
msgid ""
"Deleting a one-character word no longer erases the next word as well (:issue:"
"`4747`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3181
msgid "Token history search (Alt-Up) omits duplicate entries (:issue:`4795`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3182
msgid ""
"The ``fish_escape_delay_ms`` timeout, allowing the use of the escape key "
"both on its own and as part of a control sequence, was applied to all "
"control characters; this has been reduced to just the escape key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3185
msgid "Completing a function shows the description properly (:issue:`5206`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3186
msgid ""
"``commandline`` can now be used to set the commandline for the next command, "
"restoring a behavior in 3.4.1 (:issue:`8807`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3189
msgid ""
"``ansible``, including ``ansible-galaxy``, ``ansible-playbook`` and "
"``ansible-vault`` (:issue:`4697`)"
msgstr ""

