msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3314
msgid "Notable improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3316
msgid ""
"A new ``cdh`` (change directory using recent history) command provides a "
"more friendly alternative to prevd/nextd and pushd/popd (:issue:`2847`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3319
msgid ""
"A new ``argparse`` command is available to allow fish script to parse "
"arguments with the same behavior as builtin commands. This also includes the "
"``fish_opt`` helper command. (:issue:`4190`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3322
msgid ""
"Invalid array indexes are now silently ignored (:issue:`826`, :issue:`4127`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3323
msgid ""
"Improvements to the debugging facility, including a prompt specific to the "
"debugger (``fish_breakpoint_prompt``) and a ``status is-breakpoint`` "
"subcommand (:issue:`1310`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3326
msgid ""
"``string`` supports new ``lower`` and ``upper`` subcommands, for altering "
"the case of strings (:issue:`4080`). The case changing is not locale-aware "
"yet.- ``string escape`` has a new ``--style=xxx`` flag where ``xxx`` can be "
"``script``, ``var``, or ``url`` (:issue:`4150`), and can be reversed with "
"``string unescape`` (:issue:`3543`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3331
msgid ""
"History can now be split into sessions with the ``fish_history`` variable, "
"or not saved to disk at all (:issue:`102`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3333
msgid ""
"Read history is now controlled by the ``fish_history`` variable rather than "
"the ``--mode-name`` flag (:issue:`1504`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3335
msgid ""
"``command`` now supports an ``--all`` flag to report all directories with "
"the command. ``which`` is no longer a runtime dependency (:issue:`2778`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3338
msgid ""
"fish can run commands before starting an interactive session using the new "
"``--init-command``/``-C`` options (:issue:`4164`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3340
msgid ""
"``set`` has a new ``--show`` option to show lots of information about "
"variables (:issue:`4265`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3344 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3477
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3639
msgid "Other significant changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3346
msgid ""
"The ``COLUMNS`` and ``LINES`` environment variables are now correctly set "
"the first time ``fish_prompt`` is run (:issue:`4141`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3349
msgid ""
"``complete``\\ ’s ``--no-files`` option works as intended (:issue:`112`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3351
msgid ""
"``echo -h`` now correctly echoes ``-h`` in line with other shells (:issue:"
"`4120`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3354
msgid ""
"The ``export`` compatibility function now returns zero on success, rather "
"than always returning 1 (:issue:`4435`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3357
msgid ""
"Stop converting empty elements in MANPATH to “.” (:issue:`4158`). The "
"behavior being changed was introduced in fish 2.6.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3360
msgid ""
"``count -h`` and ``count --help`` now return 1 rather than produce command "
"help output (:issue:`4189`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3363
msgid ""
"An attempt to ``read`` which stops because too much data is available still "
"defines the variables given as parameters (:issue:`4180`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3366
msgid ""
"A regression in fish 2.4.0 which prevented ``pushd +1`` from working has "
"been fixed (:issue:`4091`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3369
msgid ""
"A regression in fish 2.6.0 where multiple ``read`` commands in non-"
"interactive scripts were broken has been fixed (:issue:`4206`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3372
msgid ""
"A regression in fish 2.6.0 involving universal variables with side-effects "
"at startup such as ``set -U fish_escape_delay_ms 10`` has been fixed (:issue:"
"`4196`)."
