msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 2.5.0 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 2.6b1 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3455
msgid "fish 2.6b1 (released May 14, 2017)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3462
msgid ""
"Jobs running in the background can now be removed from the list of jobs with "
"the new ``disown`` builtin, which behaves like the same command in other "
"shells (:issue:`2810`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3465
msgid ""
"Command substitutions now have access to the terminal, like in other shells. "
"This allows tools like ``fzf`` to work properly (:issue:`1362`, :issue:"
"`3922`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3468
msgid ""
"In cases where the operating system does not report the size of the "
"terminal, the ``COLUMNS`` and ``LINES`` environment variables are used; if "
"they are unset, a default of 80x24 is assumed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3471
msgid ""
"New French (:issue:`3772` & :issue:`3788`) and improved German (:issue:"
"`3834`) translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3472
msgid "fish no longer depends on the ``which`` external command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3479
msgid ""
"Performance improvements in launching processes, including major reductions "
"in signal blocking. Although this has been heavily tested, it may cause "
"problems in some circumstances; set the ``FISH_NO_SIGNAL_BLOCK`` variable to "
"0 in your fish configuration file to return to the old behaviour (:issue:"
"`2007`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3484
msgid ""
"Performance improvements in prompts and functions that set lots of colours (:"
"issue:`3793`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3486
msgid "The Delete key no longer deletes backwards (a regression in 2.5.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3487
msgid ""
"``functions`` supports a new ``--details`` option, which identifies where "
"the function was loaded from (:issue:`3295`), and a ``--details --verbose`` "
"option which includes the function description (:issue:`597`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3491
msgid ""
"``read`` will read up to 10 MiB by default, leaving the target variable "
"empty and exiting with status 122 if the line is too long. You can set a "
"different limit with the ``FISH_READ_BYTE_LIMIT`` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3495
msgid ""
"``read`` supports a new ``--silent`` option to hide the characters typed (:"
"issue:`838`), for when reading sensitive data from the terminal. ``read`` "
"also now accepts simple strings for the prompt (rather than scripts) with "
"the new ``-P`` and ``--prompt-str`` options (:issue:`802`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3499
msgid ""
"``export`` and ``setenv`` now understand colon-separated ``PATH``, "
"``CDPATH`` and ``MANPATH`` variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3501
msgid ""
"``setenv`` is no longer a simple alias for ``set -gx`` and will complain, "
"just like the csh version, if given more than one value (:issue:`4103`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3504
msgid "``bind`` supports a new ``--list-modes`` option (:issue:`3872`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3505
msgid ""
"``bg`` will check all of its arguments before backgrounding any jobs; any "
"invalid arguments will cause a failure, but non-existent (eg recently "
"exited) jobs are ignored (:issue:`3909`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3508
msgid ""
"``funced`` warns if the function being edited has not been modified (:issue:"
"`3961`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3510
msgid "``printf`` correctly outputs “long long” integers (:issue:`3352`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3511
msgid ""
"``status`` supports a new ``current-function`` subcommand to print the "
"current function name (:issue:`1743`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3513
msgid ""
"``string`` supports a new ``repeat`` subcommand (:issue:`3864`). ``string "
"match`` supports a new ``--entire`` option to emit the entire line matched "
"by a pattern (:issue:`3957`). ``string replace`` supports a new ``--filter`` "
"option to only emit lines which underwent a replacement (:issue:`3348`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3518
msgid ""
"``test`` supports the ``-k`` option to test for sticky bits (:issue:`733`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3519
msgid "``umask`` understands symbolic modes (:issue:`738`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3520
msgid ""
"Empty components in the ``CDPATH``, ``MANPATH`` and ``PATH`` variables are "
"now converted to “.” (:issue:`2106`, :issue:`3914`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3522
msgid ""
"New versions of ncurses (6.0 and up) wipe terminal scrollback buffers with "
"certain commands; the ``C-l`` binding tries to avoid this (:issue:`2855`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3525
msgid ""
"Some systems’ ``su`` implementations do not set the ``USER`` environment "
"variable; it is now reset for root users (:issue:`3916`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3527
msgid ""
"Under terminals which support it, bracketed paste is enabled, escaping "
"problematic characters for security and convenience (:issue:`3871`). Inside "
"single quotes (``'``), single quotes and backslashes in pasted text are "
"escaped (:issue:`967`). The ``fish_clipboard_paste`` function (bound to ``C-"
"v`` by default) is still the recommended pasting method where possible as it "
"includes this functionality and more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3533
msgid ""
"Processes in pipelines are no longer signalled as soon as one command in the "
"pipeline has completed (:issue:`1926`). This behaviour matches other shells "
"mre closely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3536
msgid ""
"All functions requiring Python work with whichever version of Python is "
"installed (:issue:`3970`). Python 3 is preferred, but Python 2.6 remains the "
"minimum version required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3539
msgid ""
"The color of the cancellation character can be controlled by the "
"``fish_color_cancel`` variable (:issue:`3963`)."
msgstr ""

