msgid "Debian 7 (EoLTS May 2018)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3613
msgid ""
"Installing newer version of fish on these systems will require building from "
"source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3617
msgid "OS X SnowLeopard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3619
msgid ""
"Starting with version 2.5, fish requires a C++11 standard library on OS X "
"10.6 (“SnowLeopard”). If this library is not installed, you will see this "
"error: ``dyld: Library not loaded: /usr/lib/libc++.1.dylib``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3623
msgid ""
"MacPorts is the easiest way to obtain this library. After installing the "
"SnowLeopard MacPorts release from the install page, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3628
msgid "sudo port -v install libcxx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3630
msgid ""
"Now fish should launch successfully. (Please open an issue if it does not.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3633
msgid ""
"This is only necessary on 10.6. OS X 10.7 and later include the required "
"library by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3641
msgid ""
"Attempting to exit with running processes in the background produces a "
"warning, then signals them to terminate if a second attempt to exit is made. "
"This brings the behaviour for running background processes into line with "
"stopped processes. (:issue:`3497`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3645
msgid ""
"``random`` can now have start, stop and step values specified, or the new "
"``choice`` subcommand can be used to pick an argument from a list (:issue:"
"`3619`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3648
msgid ""
"A new key bindings preset, ``fish_hybrid_key_bindings``, including all the "
"Emacs-style and Vi-style bindings, which behaves like "
"``fish_vi_key_bindings`` in fish 2.3.0 (:issue:`3556`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3651
msgid ""
"``function`` now returns an error when called with invalid options, rather "
"than defining the function anyway (:issue:`3574`). This was a regression "
"present in fish 2.3 and 2.4.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3654
msgid ""
"fish no longer prints a warning when it identifies a running instance of an "
"old version (2.1.0 and earlier). Changes to universal variables may not "
"propagate between these old versions and 2.5b1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3657
msgid ""
"Improved compatibility with Android (:issue:`3585`), MSYS/mingw (:issue:"
"`2360`), and Solaris (:issue:`3456`, :issue:`3340`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3659
msgid ""
"Like other shells, the ``test`` built-in now returns an error for numeric "
"operations on invalid integers (:issue:`3346`, :issue:`3581`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3661
msgid ""
"``complete`` no longer recognises ``--authoritative`` and ``--"
"unauthoritative`` options, and they are marked as obsolete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3663
msgid ""
"``status`` accepts subcommands, and should be used like ``status is-"
"interactive``. The old options continue to be supported for the foreseeable "
"future (:issue:`3526`), although only one subcommand or option can be "
"specified at a time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3667
msgid ""
"Selection mode (used with “begin-selection”) no longer selects a character "
"the cursor does not move over (:issue:`3684`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3669
msgid ""
"List indexes are handled better, and a bit more liberally in some cases "
"(``echo $PATH[1 .. 3]`` is now valid) (:issue:`3579`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3671
msgid ""
"The ``fish_mode_prompt`` function is now simply a stub around "
"``fish_default_mode_prompt``, which allows the mode prompt to be included "
"more easily in customised prompt functions (:issue:`3641`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3680
msgid ""
"``alias``, run without options or arguments, lists all defined aliases, and "
"aliases now include a description in the function signature that identifies "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3683
msgid "``complete`` accepts empty strings as descriptions (:issue:`3557`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3684
msgid ""
"``command`` accepts ``-q``/``--quiet`` in combination with ``--search`` (:"
"issue:`3591`), providing a simple way of checking whether a command exists "
"in scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3687
msgid ""
"Abbreviations can now be renamed with ``abbr --rename OLD_KEY NEW_KEY`` (:"
"issue:`3610`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3689
msgid ""
"The command synopses printed by ``--help`` options work better with copying "
"and pasting (:issue:`2673`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3691
msgid ""
"``help`` launches the browser specified by the ``$fish_help_browser "
"variable`` if it is set (:issue:`3131`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3693
msgid ""
"History merging could lose items under certain circumstances and is now "
"fixed (:issue:`3496`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3695
msgid ""
"The ``$status`` variable is now set to 123 when a syntactically invalid "
"command is entered (:issue:`3616`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3697
msgid ""
"Exiting fish now signals all background processes to terminate, not just "
"stopped jobs (:issue:`3497`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3699
msgid ""
"A new ``prompt_hostname`` function which prints a hostname suitable for use "
"in prompts (:issue:`3482`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3701
msgid ""
"The ``__fish_man_page`` function (bound to Alt-h by default) now tries to "
"recognize subcommands (e.g. ``git add`` will now open the “git-add” man "
"page) (:issue:`3678`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3704
msgid ""
"A new function ``edit_command_buffer`` (bound to Alt-e & Alt-v by default) "
"to edit the command buffer in an external editor (:issue:`1215`, :issue:"
"`3627`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3707
msgid ""
"``set_color`` now supports italics (``--italics``), dim (``--dim``) and "
"reverse (``--reverse``) modes (:issue:`3650`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3709
msgid ""
"Filesystems with very slow locking (eg incorrectly-configured NFS) will no "
"longer slow fish down (:issue:`685`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3711
msgid ""
"Improved completions for ``apt`` (:issue:`3695`), ``fusermount`` (:issue:"
"`3642`), ``make`` (:issue:`3628`), ``netctl-auto`` (:issue:`3378`), "
"``nmcli`` (:issue:`3648`), ``pygmentize`` (:issue:`3378`), and ``tar`` (:"
