#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3739
msgid "fish 2.4.0 (released November 8, 2016)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3741
msgid "There are no major changes between 2.4b1 and 2.4.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3748
msgid ""
"The documentation is now generated properly and with the correct version "
"identifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3750
msgid ""
"Automatic cursor changes are now only enabled on the subset of XTerm "
"versions known to support them, resolving a problem where older versions "
"printed garbage to the terminal before and after every prompt (:issue:"
"`3499`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3754
msgid "Improved the title set in Apple Terminal.app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3755
msgid ""
"Added completions for ``defaults`` and improved completions for ``diskutil`` "
"(:issue:`3478`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3761
msgid "fish 2.4b1 (released October 18, 2016)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3764 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3865
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3932 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4062
msgid "Significant changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3766
msgid ""
"The clipboard integration has been revamped with explicit bindings. The "
"killring commands no longer copy from, or paste to, the X11 clipboard - use "
"the new copy (``C-x``) and paste (``C-v``) bindings instead. The clipboard "
"is now available on OS X as well as systems using X11 (e.g. Linux). (:issue:"
"`3061`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3771
msgid ""
"``history`` uses subcommands (``history delete``) rather than options "
"(``history --delete``) for its actions (:issue:`3367`). You can no longer "
"specify multiple actions via flags (e.g., ``history --delete --save "
"something``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3775
msgid ""
"New ``history`` options have been added, including ``--max=n`` to limit the "
"number of history entries, ``--show-time`` option to show timestamps (:issue:"
"`3175`, :issue:`3244`), and ``--null`` to null terminate history entries in "
"the search output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3779
msgid ""
"``history search`` is now case-insensitive by default (which also affects "
"``history delete``) (:issue:`3236`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3781
msgid ""
"``history delete`` now correctly handles multiline commands (:issue:`31`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3782
msgid ""
"Vi-style bindings no longer include all of the default emacs-style bindings; "
"instead, they share some definitions (:issue:`3068`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3784
msgid ""
"If there is no locale set in the environment, various known system "
"configuration files will be checked for a default. If no locale can be "
"found, ``en_US-UTF.8`` will be used (:issue:`277`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3787
msgid ""
"A number followed by a caret (e.g. ``5^``) is no longer treated as a "
"redirection (:issue:`1873`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3789
msgid ""
"The ``$version`` special variable can be overwritten, so that it can be used "
"for other purposes if required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3797
msgid ""
"The ``fish_realpath`` builtin has been renamed to ``realpath`` and made "
"compatible with GNU ``realpath`` when run without arguments (:issue:`3400`). "
"It is used only for systems without a ``realpath`` or ``grealpath`` utility "
"(:issue:`3374`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3801
msgid ""
"Improved color handling on terminals/consoles with 8-16 colors, particularly "
"the use of bright named color (:issue:`3176`, :issue:`3260`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3803
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` can now read from files given as arguments, rather than just "
"standard input (:issue:`3037`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3805
msgid ""
"Fuzzy tab completions behave in a less surprising manner (:issue:`3090`, :"
"issue:`3211`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3807
msgid "``jobs`` should only print its header line once (:issue:`3127`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3808
msgid ""
"Wildcards in redirections are highlighted appropriately (:issue:`2789`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3809
msgid ""
"Suggestions will be offered more often, like after removing characters (:"
"issue:`3069`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3811
msgid ""
"``history --merge`` now correctly interleaves items in chronological order (:"
"issue:`2312`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3813
msgid ""
"Options for ``fish_indent`` have been aligned with the other binaries - in "
"particular, ``-d`` now means ``--debug``. The ``--dump`` option has been "
"renamed to ``--dump-parse-tree`` (:issue:`3191`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3816
msgid ""
"The display of bindings in the Web-based configuration has been greatly "
"improved (:issue:`3325`), as has the rendering of prompts (:issue:`2924`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3818
msgid ""
"fish should no longer hang using 100% CPU in the C locale (:issue:`3214`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3819
msgid ""
"A bug in FreeBSD 11 & 12, Dragonfly BSD & illumos prevented fish from "
"working correctly on these platforms under UTF-8 locales; fish now avoids "
"the buggy behaviour (:issue:`3050`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3822
msgid ""
"Prompts which show git repository information (via ``__fish_git_prompt``) "
"are faster in large repositories (:issue:`3294`) and slow filesystems (:"
"issue:`3083`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3825
msgid ""
"fish 2.3.0 reintroduced a problem where the greeting was printed even when "
"using ``read``; this has been corrected again (:issue:`3261`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3827
msgid ""
"Vi mode changes the cursor depending on the current mode (:issue:`3215`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3828
msgid ""
"Command lines with escaped space characters at the end tab-complete "
"correctly (:issue:`2447`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3832
msgid "``arcanist`` (:issue:`3256`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3833
msgid "``connmanctl`` (:issue:`3419`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3834
msgid "``figlet`` (:issue:`3378`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3835
msgid "``mdbook`` (:issue:`3378`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3836
msgid "``ninja`` (:issue:`3415`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3837
msgid "``p4``, the Perforce client (:issue:`3314`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3838
msgid "``pygmentize`` (:issue:`3378`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3839
msgid "``ranger`` (:issue:`3378`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3841
msgid ""
"Improved completions for ``aura`` (:issue:`3297`), ``abbr`` (:issue:`3267`), "
"``brew`` (:issue:`3309`), ``chown`` (:issue:`3380`, :issue:`3383`),\\ "
"``cygport`` (:issue:`3392`), ``git`` (:issue:`3274`, :issue:`3226`, :issue:"
"`3225`, :issue:`3094`, :issue:`3087`, :issue:`3035`, :issue:`3021`, :issue:"
"`2982`, :issue:`3230`), ``kill`` & ``pkill`` (:issue:`3200`), ``screen`` (:"
"issue:`3271`), ``wget`` (:issue:`3470`), and ``xz`` (:issue:`3378`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3846
msgid ""
"Distributors, packagers and developers will notice that the build process "
"produces more succinct output by default; use ``make V=1`` to get verbose "
"output (:issue:`3248`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3849
msgid ""
"Improved compatibility with minor platforms including musl (:issue:`2988`), "
"Cygwin (:issue:`2993`), Android (:issue:`3441`, :issue:`3442`), Haiku (:"
"issue:`3322`) and Solaris ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3855
msgid "fish 2.3.1 (released July 3, 2016)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3857
msgid ""
"This is a functionality and bugfix release. This release does not contain "
"all the changes to fish since the last release, but fixes a number of issues "
"directly affecting users at present and includes a small number of new "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3867
msgid ""
"A new ``fish_key_reader`` binary for decoding interactive keypresses (:issue:"
"`2991`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3869
msgid ""
"``fish_mode_prompt`` has been updated to reflect the changes in the way the "
"Vi input mode is set up (:issue:`3067`), making this more reliable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3871
msgid ""
"``fish_config`` can now properly be launched from the OS X app bundle (:"
"issue:`3140`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3879
msgid ""
"Extra lines were sometimes inserted into the output under Windows (Cygwin "
"and Microsoft Windows Subsystem for Linux) due to TTY timestamps not being "
"updated (:issue:`2859`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3882
msgid ""
"The ``string`` builtin’s ``match`` mode now handles the combination of ``-"
"rnv`` (match, invert and count) correctly (:issue:`3098`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3884
msgid ""
"Improvements to TTY special character handling (:issue:`3064`), locale "
"handling (:issue:`3124`) and terminal environment variable handling (:issue:"
"`3060`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3886
msgid ""
"Work towards handling the terminal modes for external commands launched from "
"initialisation files (:issue:`2980`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3888
msgid ""
"Ease the upgrade path from fish 2.2.0 and before by warning users to restart "
"fish if the ``string`` builtin is not available (:issue:`3057`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3890
msgid "``type -a`` now syntax-colorizes function source output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3891
msgid ""
"Added completions for ``alsamixer``, ``godoc``, ``gofmt``, ``goimports``, "
"``gorename``, ``lscpu``, ``mkdir``, ``modinfo``, ``netctl-auto``, "
"``poweroff``, ``termite``, ``udisksctl`` and ``xz`` (:issue:`3123`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3895
msgid ""
"Improved completions for ``apt`` (:issue:`3097`), ``aura`` (:issue:`3102`),"
"\\ ``git`` (:issue:`3114`), ``npm`` (:issue:`3158`), ``string`` and "
"``suspend`` (:issue:`3154`)."
msgstr ""

