#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4057
msgid "fish 2.2.0 (released July 12, 2015)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4064
msgid ""
"Abbreviations: the new ``abbr`` command allows for interactively-expanded "
"abbreviations, allowing quick access to frequently-used commands (:issue:"
"`731`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4067
msgid ""
"Vi mode: run ``fish_vi_mode`` to switch fish into the key bindings and "
"prompt familiar to users of the Vi editor (:issue:`65`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4069
msgid ""
"New inline and interactive pager, which will be familiar to users of zsh (:"
"issue:`291`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4071
msgid ""
"Underlying architectural changes: the ``fishd`` universal variable server "
"has been removed as it was a source of many bugs and security problems. "
"Notably, old fish sessions will not be able to communicate universal "
"variable changes with new fish sessions. For best results, restart all "
"running instances of ``fish``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4076
msgid ""
"The web-based configuration tool has been redesigned, featuring a prompt "
"theme chooser and other improvements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4078
msgid "New German, Brazilian Portuguese, and Chinese translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4085
msgid ""
"These are kept to a minimum, but either change undocumented features or are "
"too hard to use in their existing forms. These changes may break existing "
"scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4089
msgid ""
"``commandline`` no longer interprets functions “in reverse”, instead "
"behaving as expected (:issue:`1567`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4091
msgid ""
"The previously-undocumented ``CMD_DURATION`` variable is now set for all "
"commands and contains the execution time of the last command in milliseconds "
"(:issue:`1585`). It is no longer exported to other commands (:issue:`1896`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4095
msgid ""
"``if`` / ``else`` conditional statements now return values consistent with "
"the Single Unix Specification, like other shells (:issue:`1443`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4097
msgid ""
"A new “top-level” local scope has been added, allowing local variables "
"declared on the commandline to be visible to subsequent commands. (:issue:"
"`1908`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4106
msgid ""
"New documentation design (:issue:`1662`), which requires a Doxygen version "
"1.8.7 or newer to build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4108
msgid ""
"Fish now defines a default directory for other packages to provide "
"completions. By default this is ``/usr/share/fish/vendor-completions.d``; on "
"systems with ``pkgconfig`` installed this path is discoverable with ``pkg-"
"config --variable completionsdir fish``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4113
msgid ""
"A new parser removes many bugs; all existing syntax should keep working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4115
msgid ""
"New ``fish_preexec`` and ``fish_postexec`` events are fired before and after "
"job execution respectively (:issue:`1549`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4117
msgid ""
"Unmatched wildcards no longer prevent a job from running. Wildcards used "
"interactively will still print an error, but the job will proceed and the "
"wildcard will expand to zero arguments (:issue:`1482`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4120
msgid ""
"The ``.`` command is deprecated and the ``source`` command is preferred (:"
"issue:`310`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4122
msgid ""
"``bind`` supports “bind modes”, which allows bindings to be set for a "
"particular named mode, to support the implementation of Vi mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4124
msgid ""
"A new ``export`` alias, which behaves like other shells (:issue:`1833`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4125
msgid ""
"``command`` has a new ``--search`` option to print the name of the disk file "
"that would be executed, like other shells’ ``command -v`` (:issue:`1540`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4128
msgid ""
"``commandline`` has a new ``--paging-mode`` option to support the new pager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4130
msgid ""
"``complete`` has a new ``--wraps`` option, which allows a command to "
"(recursively) inherit the completions of a wrapped command (:issue:`393`), "
"and ``complete -e`` now correctly erases completions (:issue:`380`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4133
msgid ""
"Completions are now generated from manual pages by default on the first run "
"of fish (:issue:`997`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4135
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` can now produce colorized (``--ansi``) and HTML (``--html``) "
"output (:issue:`1827`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4137
msgid ""
"``functions --erase`` now prevents autoloaded functions from being reloaded "
"in the current session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4139
msgid ""
"``history`` has a new ``--merge`` option, to incorporate history from other "
"sessions into the current session (:issue:`825`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4141
msgid "``jobs`` returns 1 if there are no active jobs (:issue:`1484`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4142
msgid "``read`` has several new options:"
msgstr ""

