#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4180
msgid "fish 2.1.2 (released Feb 24, 2015)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4182
msgid ""
"fish 2.1.2 contains a workaround for a filesystem bug in Mac OS X Yosemite. :"
"issue:`1859`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4185
msgid ""
"Specifically, after installing fish 2.1.1 and then rebooting, “Verify Disk” "
"in Disk Utility will report “Invalid number of hard links.” We don’t have "
"any reports of data loss or other adverse consequences. fish 2.1.2 avoids "
"triggering the bug, but does not repair an already affected filesystem. To "
"repair the filesystem, you can boot into Recovery Mode and use Repair Disk "
"from Disk Utility. Linux and versions of OS X prior to Yosemite are believed "
"to be unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4193
msgid "There are no other changes in this release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4198
msgid "fish 2.1.1 (released September 26, 2014)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4200
msgid ""
"**Important:** if you are upgrading, stop all running instances of ``fishd`` "
"as soon as possible after installing this release; it will be restarted "
"automatically. On most systems, there will be no further action required. "
"Note that some environments (where ``XDG_RUNTIME_DIR`` is set), such as "
"Fedora 20, will require a restart of all running fish processes before "
"universal variables work as intended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4207
msgid ""
"Distributors are highly encouraged to call ``killall fishd``, ``pkill "
"fishd`` or similar in installation scripts, or to warn their users to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4212
msgid "Security fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4214
msgid ""
"The fish_config web interface now uses an authentication token to protect "
"requests and only responds to requests from the local machine with this "
"token, preventing a remote code execution attack. (closing CVE-2014-2914). :"
"issue:`1438`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4218
msgid ""
"``psub`` and ``funced`` are no longer vulnerable to attacks which allow "
"local privilege escalation and data tampering (closing CVE-2014-2906 and "
"CVE-2014-3856). :issue:`1437`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4221
msgid ""
"``fishd`` uses a secure path for its socket, preventing a local privilege "
"escalation attack (closing CVE-2014-2905). :issue:`1436`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4223
msgid ""
"``__fish_print_packages`` is no longer vulnerable to attacks which would "
"allow local privilege escalation and data tampering (closing "
"CVE-2014-3219). :issue:`1440`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4228
msgid "Other fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4230
msgid ""
"``fishd`` now ignores SIGPIPE, fixing crashes using tools like GNU Parallel "
"and which occurred more often as a result of the other ``fishd`` changes. :"
"issue:`1084` & :issue:`1690`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4237
msgid "fish 2.1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4244
msgid "**Tab completions will fuzzy-match files.** :issue:`568`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4246
msgid ""
"When tab-completing a file, fish will first attempt prefix matches (``foo`` "
"matches ``foobar``), then substring matches (``ooba`` matches ``foobar``), "
"and lastly subsequence matches (``fbr`` matches ``foobar``). For example, in "
"a directory with files foo1.txt, foo2.txt, foo3.txt…, you can type only the "
"numeric part and hit tab to fill in the rest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4253
msgid ""
"This feature is implemented for files and executables. It is not yet "
"implemented for options (like ``--foobar``), and not yet implemented across "
"path components (like ``/u/l/b`` to match ``/usr/local/bin``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4257
msgid ""
"**Redirections now work better across pipelines.** :issue:`110`, :issue:`877`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4259
msgid ""
"In particular, you can pipe stderr and stdout together, for example, with "
"``cmd ^&1 | tee log.txt``, or the more familiar ``cmd 2>&1 | tee log.txt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4263
msgid ""
"**A single ``%`` now expands to the last job backgrounded.** :issue:`1008`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4265
msgid ""
"Previously, a single ``%`` would pid-expand to either all backgrounded jobs, "
"or all jobs owned by your user. Now it expands to the last job backgrounded. "
"If no job is in the background, it will fail to expand. In particular, ``fg "
"%`` can be used to put the most recent background job in the foreground."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4272 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4389
msgid "Other Notable Fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4274
msgid ""
"alt-U and alt+C now uppercase and capitalize words, respectively. :issue:"
"`995`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4277
msgid "VTE based terminals should now know the working directory. :issue:`906`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4279
msgid "The autotools build now works on Mavericks. :issue:`968`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4281
msgid ""
"The end-of-line binding (ctrl+E) now accepts autosuggestions. :issue:`932`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4283
msgid ""
"Directories in ``/etc/paths`` (used on OS X) are now prepended instead of "
"appended, similar to other shells. :issue:`927`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4286
msgid ""
"Option-right-arrow (used for partial autosuggestion completion) now works on "
"iTerm2. :issue:`920`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4289
msgid ""
"Tab completions now work properly within nested subcommands. :issue:`913`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4291
msgid "``printf`` supports ``\\e``, the escape character. :issue:`910`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4293
msgid "``fish_config history`` no longer shows duplicate items. :issue:`900`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4295
msgid ""
"``$fish_user_paths`` is now prepended to $PATH instead of appended. :issue:"
"`888`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4298
msgid "Jobs complete when all processes complete. :issue:`876`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4300
msgid ""
"For example, in previous versions of fish, ``sleep 10 | echo Done`` returns "
"control immediately, because echo does not read from stdin. Now it does not "
"complete until sleep exits (presumably after 10 seconds)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4305
msgid "Better error reporting for square brackets. :issue:`875`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4307
msgid ""
"fish no longer tries to add ``/bin`` to ``$PATH`` unless PATH is totally "
"empty. :issue:`852`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4310
msgid ""
"History token substitution (alt-up) now works correctly inside subshells. :"
"issue:`833`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4313
msgid ""
"Flow control is now disabled, freeing up ctrl-S and ctrl-Q for other uses. :"
"issue:`814`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4316
msgid ""
"sh-style variable setting like ``foo=bar`` now produces better error "
"messages. :issue:`809`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4319
msgid "Commands with wildcards no longer produce autosuggestions. :issue:`785`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4321
msgid ""
"funced no longer freaks out when supplied with no arguments. :issue:`780`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4323
msgid ""
"fish.app now works correctly in a directory containing spaces. :issue:`774`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4325
msgid ""
"Tab completion cycling no longer occasionally fails to repaint. :issue:`765`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4327
msgid "Comments now work in eval’d strings. :issue:`684`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4329
msgid ""
"History search (up-arrow) now shows the item matching the autosuggestion, if "
"that autosuggestion was truncated. :issue:`650`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4332
msgid "Ctrl-T now transposes characters, as in other shells. :issue:`128`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4337
msgid "fish 2.0.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4344
msgid ""
"**Command substitutions now modify ``$status`` :issue:`547`.** Previously "
"the exit status of command substitutions (like ``(pwd)``) was ignored; "
"however now it modifies $status. Furthermore, the ``set`` command now only "
"sets $status on failure; it is untouched on success. This allows for the "
"following pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4350
msgid ""
"if set python_path (which python)\n"
"   ...\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4356
msgid ""
"Because set does not modify $status on success, the if branch effectively "
"tests whether ``which`` succeeded, and if so, whether the ``set`` also "
"succeeded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4360
msgid ""
"Improvements to PATH handling. There is a new variable, fish_user_paths, "
"which can be set universally, and whose contents are appended to $PATH :"
"issue:`527`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4364
msgid "/etc/paths and /etc/paths.d are now respected on OS X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4365
msgid "fish no longer modifies $PATH to find its own binaries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4367
msgid ""
"**Long lines no longer use ellipsis for line breaks**, and copy and paste "
"should no longer include a newline even if the line was broken :issue:`300`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4371
msgid ""
"**New syntax for index ranges** (sometimes known as “slices”) :issue:`212`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4373
msgid "**fish now supports an ``else if`` statement** :issue:`134`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4375
msgid "**Process and pid completion now works on OS X** :issue:`129`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4377
msgid ""
"**fish is now relocatable**, and no longer depends on compiled-in paths :"
"issue:`125`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4380
msgid ""
"**fish now supports a right prompt (RPROMPT)** through the fish_right_prompt "
"function :issue:`80`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4383
msgid ""
"**fish now uses posix_spawn instead of fork when possible**, which is much "
"faster on BSD and OS X :issue:`11`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4391
msgid "Updated VCS completions (darcs, cvs, svn, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4392
msgid "Avoid calling getcwd on the main thread, as it can hang :issue:`696`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4393
msgid "Control-D (forward delete) no longer stops at a period :issue:`667`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4394
msgid "Completions for many new commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4395
msgid "fish now respects rxvt’s unique keybindings :issue:`657`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4396
msgid ""
"xsel is no longer built as part of fish. It will still be invoked if "
